var storyContent = {"inkVersion":21,"root":[["^Stonecross, Rybnik, and the fields between them sit on land that survived when others didn’t.","\n","^Bath steam rises from bloody tiles. Red flowers grow where bodies once burned. Soldiers pitch tents where the dead were meant to lie undisturbed. On the surface, this is just another corner of war-worn Velen—quiet villages, a garrison, a few contracts nailed to posts. Underneath, old bargains, buried guilt, and unfinished debts are beginning to stir.","\n","^This three-part quest arc explores how survival is paid for, and who pays when the bill comes due. You’ll investigate crimes that aren’t always murders, murders that aren't always crimes, and decide whether justice belongs to steel, truth, or something between. Combat is possible, but rarely clean. Many outcomes hinge on what you notice, who you speak with, and what you’re willing to let continue. There are no perfect resolutions here.","\n","^When you’re ready, press START and ride into Stonecross.","\n","ev","str","^START","/str","/ev",{"*":"0.c-0","flg":4},{"c-0":["\n",{"->":"q1_steam_and_secrets_entry"},{"->":"0.g-0"},{"#f":5}],"g-0":["done",{"#f":5}]}],"done",{"q1_steam_and_secrets_entry":[["ev",false,"/ev",{"VAR=":"Q1_COMPLETED","re":true},"^The town of Stonecross sits low on the riverbank, roofs hunched under a leaden sky. The war has not quite reached it, not in the way of burning thatch or nighttime raids, but black-and-gold banners flap on the far slope where a Nilfgaardian garrison has made camp. An omen of that bloody future not being long off.","\n","^Closer to the river, steam spills from a squat stone building, windows fogged. A hand-painted board swings above the door, wet from mist and rain.","\n","^STONECROSS BATHS – HOT WATER, CLEAN LINEN, QUIET","\n","^By the notice board, a sheet of parchment has been nailed crosswise. The ink has run in the drizzle, but the words still catch your eye.","\n","^\"Help Wanted: Strange doings at the baths. Two patrons injured in private rooms. Seeking professionals. Decent pay. No charlatans. Ask for Oszkar at Stonecross Baths.\"","\n","ev","str","^Head straight to the baths and ask for Oszkar.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":4},"ev","str","^Linger by the board, listen to gossip first.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-1","flg":4},{"c-0":["\n",{"->":"q1_initial_briefing"},{"#f":5}],"c-1":["^ ","\n",{"->":"q1_bath_gossip"},{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"q1_bath_gossip":[["^A pair of peasants in mud-caked boots argue nearby, voices low and eager.","\n","^\"—burned so bad the skin slid off like boiled pig fat, I tell you.\"","\n","^\"You didn't see it.\"","\n","^\"Didn't have to. My cousin's boy carries the coal. Says they had to peel him off the tiles.\"","\n","^Another spits into the mud.","\n","^\"And Lida? Wakes choking in the night, they say. Won't go near a bath anymore. Not like she had before.\"","\n","^There's a roar of laughter before a wagoner leans in. \"If the baths close, garrison'll blame the town. Already muttering the place is cursed.\"","\n","^You fold the notice and tuck it away.","\n","ev","str","^Enough. Go to the baths and find Oszkar.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":4},{"c-0":["\n",{"->":"q1_initial_briefing"},{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"q1_initial_briefing":[["ev",true,"/ev",{"VAR=":"q1_spoke_to_oszkar_initial","re":true},"^Inside, the air is thick with steam and wet stone. Voices echo off tiled walls—locals in stained linen, Nilfgaardian soldiers all stripped of armor and rank. The sanctuary smells of soap, sweat, and boiling river water.","\n","^At the front desk, a narrow-shouldered man in a damp shirt wrings his hands over a ledger. Perpetually wet long hair slicked back by necessity, not vanity. When he looks up and sees the medallion at your throat, his expression tightens.","\n","^\"Oszkar Mielnik,\" he says. \"Owner.\" His eyes flick past you to the door. \"Best we speak aside, witcher. No sense spooking paying folk.\"","\n","^He draws you behind a bead curtain into a small office that smells of mildew and lamp oil. He talks fast, gaze always skittering away from yours.","\n","^\"First was Tomas Neyman. Soldier from the camp. Boiled in his tub like a meat stew, water went from warm to screaming in a heartbeat. Door barred from inside.\"","\n","^\"Then Lida. My senior attendant. Alone in a private room, checking towels. Towel snaps round her throat from behind, she says, starts strangling her. Another girl heard it, broke in before she choked. Neck's still the color of old plums, else I'd have thought it all made up.\"","\n","^He rubs at his own throat.","\n","^\"And this morning...\"","\n","^You wait.","\n","^\"This morning I barred a door and didn't let the guard in,\" he mutters. \"Found a soldier from the camp crushed under a brazier. Door bolted. Room locked. I sent the girls home. Haven't told Captain Janrek yet.\"","\n","^He looks up at you. Wary. Hopeful. Afraid.","\n","^\"Contract's simple. Find the cause. End it. Quietly. If the baths close, half the garrison'll have my arse.\"","\n","^You haggle. He winces at your first number, sputters at the second, finally nods at the third with a noise like a man swallowing a stone.","\n","^\"Fine. Fine. Just...do it quick. Before some fool starts shouting 'curse' in the main hall.\"","\n","ev","str","^Agree to take the contract and start investigating.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":4},"ev","str","^Push Oszkar harder before you start. Ask what he's not telling you.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-1","flg":4},{"c-0":["\n",{"->":"q1_investigation_hub"},{"#f":5}],"c-1":["\n",{"->":"q1_push_oszkar_secret"},{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"q1_push_oszkar_secret":[["^You let the silence stretch. His fingers drum on warped wood.","\n","^\"Three incidents,\" you say. \"All in private rooms. All with doors locked from within. You waited to mention the corpse. Anything else you're forgetting?\"","\n","^A muscle jumps in his cheek.","\n","^\"Forgot nothing,\" he snaps, too quick. \"Only—I only thought best to handle matters in order. Oldest first. That's all.\"","\n","^You hear his pulse beating like a trapped bird in his throat.","\n","^\"Two of the victims were soldiers. From the garrison camp,\" you say. \"Special guests?\"","\n","^His eyes dart away.","\n","^\"We get officers, yes. Nilfgaardian coin's still coin. Pay well for a hot soak far from latrine stink. A fair girl or two, procured by Wenda. He's the dead one.\"","\n","^He clamps his mouth shut. The lie isn't in what he says. It's in everything he doesn't.","\n","^You could press harder. But bodies cool.","\n","ev","str","^Let it go. For now. Go see the dead soldier.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":4},"ev","str","^Threaten him with the captain and local guards if he keeps holding back.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-1","flg":4},{"c-0":["\n",{"->":"q1_investigation_hub"},{"#f":5}],"c-1":["\n",{"->":"q1_oszkar_flustered"},{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"q1_oszkar_flustered":["^\"You can either tell me,\" you say, \"or I can ask the captain, in front of his men, why his soldiers are dying in your steam rooms.\"","\n","^Oszkar pales. For a heartbeat, he seems ready to bolt.","\n","^\"No,\" he hisses. \"No. The captain... This is my house. My problem.\"","\n","^He swallows.","\n","^\"There were...special nights,\" he blurts. \"Baths cleared, no locals, just officers. Arranged through Wenda. Coin changed hands. I didn't ask who with who. It's war, you understand.\"","\n","^His gaze clings to you. Begging you to move on.","\n","^\"That's all?\"","\n","^\"For now,\" he says hoarsely. \"You'll find the rest in the tiles, witcher.\"","\n","^He straightens, wipes his hands.","\n",{"->":"q1_investigation_hub"},{"#f":1}],"q1_investigation_hub":[["^Steam hangs low in the main corridor, blurring lantern light. Somewhere a bucket clatters, followed by a hissed curse. You stand at the crossroads of the bathhouse: one way to private rooms, another down toward the furnace, a third back to reception and the door.","\n","^The dead soldier waits behind a bolted door. The scalded quartermaster groans in an inn room nearby. Lida chokes on her own nightmares in a rented bed.","\n","ev",{"VAR?":"q1_saw_soldier_body"},"!","/ev",[{"->":".^.b","c":true},{"b":["\n","ev","str","^Inspect the dead soldier's locked bath chamber.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":4},{"->":".^.^.^.9"},{"c-0":["\n",{"->":"q1_soldier_bath"},{"#f":5}]}]}],"nop","\n","ev",{"VAR?":"q1_spoke_to_neyman"},"!","/ev",[{"->":".^.b","c":true},{"b":["\n","ev","str","^Visit the scalded quartermaster, Tomas Neyman.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":4},{"->":".^.^.^.16"},{"c-0":["\n",{"->":"q1_tomas_neyman"},{"#f":5}]}]}],"nop","\n","ev",{"VAR?":"q1_spoke_to_lida"},"!","/ev",[{"->":".^.b","c":true},{"b":["\n","ev","str","^Visit Lida Sarnova, the strangled attendant.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":4},{"->":".^.^.^.23"},{"c-0":["\n",{"->":"q1_lida_sarnova"},{"#f":5}]}]}],"nop","\n","ev",{"VAR?":"q1_spoke_to_lida"},{"VAR?":"q1_identified_bannik"},"!","&&","/ev",[{"->":".^.b","c":true},{"b":["\n","ev","str","^Piece together the pattern—decide what kind of spirit you're dealing with.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":4},{"->":".^.^.^.32"},{"c-0":["\n",{"->":"q1_identify_bannik"},{"#f":5}]}]}],"nop","\n","ev",{"VAR?":"q1_identified_bannik"},{"VAR?":"q1_spoke_to_bannik"},"!","&&",{"VAR?":"q1_spoke_to_lida"},"&&",{"VAR?":"q1_spoke_to_neyman"},"&&",{"VAR?":"q1_saw_soldier_body"},"&&","/ev",[{"->":".^.b","c":true},{"b":["\n","ev","str","^You're certain now. Clear the baths and call the thing out.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":4},{"->":".^.^.^.47"},{"c-0":["\n",{"->":"q1_bannik_confrontation_entry"},{"#f":5}]}]}],"nop","\n","ev",{"VAR?":"q1_spoke_to_lida"},{"VAR?":"q1_spoke_to_agata"},"!","&&","/ev",[{"->":".^.b","c":true},{"b":["\n","ev","str","^Ride to the Nilfgaardian garrison to ask after the midwife Agata.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":4},{"->":".^.^.^.56"},{"c-0":["\n",{"->":"q1_midwife_path_entry"},{"#f":5}]}]}],"nop","\n","ev",{"VAR?":"q1_saw_soldier_body"},{"VAR?":"q1_oszkar_confronted"},"!","&&","/ev",[{"->":".^.b","c":true},{"b":["\n","ev","str","^Confront Oszkar with what you've seen so far.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":4},{"->":".^.^.^.65"},{"c-0":["^ ","\n",{"->":"q1_confront_oszkar"},{"#f":5}]}]}],"nop","\n","ev",{"VAR?":"q1_spoke_to_bannik"},{"VAR?":"q1_can_resolve"},"!","&&","/ev",[{"->":".^.b","c":true},{"b":["\n","ev",true,"/ev",{"VAR=":"q1_can_resolve","re":true},{"->":".^.^.^.74"},null]}],"nop","\n","ev",{"VAR?":"q1_can_resolve"},"/ev",[{"->":".^.b","c":true},{"b":["\n","ev","str","^Decide how justice should fall—in human hands, spirit's, or your own.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":4},{"->":".^.^.^.80"},{"c-0":["\n",{"->":"q1_resolution_hub"},{"#f":5}]}]}],"nop","\n","ev","str","^Leave the bathhouse for now.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":4},{"c-0":["\n","^You step out into the river wind. The steam stays clinging to your hair, your thoughts.","\n",{"->":".^.^.^"},{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"q1_soldier_bath":[["ev",true,"/ev",{"VAR=":"q1_saw_soldier_body","re":true},"^Oszkar fumbles with the key, hands slick. The bolt scrapes back. The smell hits first: scorched fat and cheap soap.","\n","^Inside, the private room is the size of a peasant's hut. Tub, bench, lattice-window fogged opaque. A brazier lies overturned in the center of the floor, belly-down, iron lip buried in meat and tile.","\n","^The soldier, still in a bath towel, lies under it, spinal column crushed inward, stomach caved in like a kicked pumpkin. His face is oddly untouched. His eyes are still open, staring at the ceiling as if puzzled.","\n","^You crouch and activate Witcher Senses.","\n","^The brazier's wall-mount is bent outward, not down. It didn't simply fall. Force—sharp, deliberate—tore it free and hurled it. Why? If it fell naturally, straight down, it would have crushed his skull: a more convincing way to kill than through the abdomen. It took effort to meet the belly of this man.","\n","^No pry marks on the frame of the door. No scuffs on the sill. No second set of footprints on the steam-streaked floor. Just his.","\n","^You run fingers along the brazier's edge. Damp ash clings. One thing more glitters in the corner where tile meets wall: a small tuft of white hair, sodden, unlike the soldier's close-cropped dark stubble.","\n","^You pluck it up. It's coarse. Old.","\n","^On a low stool by the tub, papers sit in an untidy heap. Lists of officer privileges, times and signatures. Wenda's and Neyman's name more than once next to notes about \"private access\" nights.","\n","ev","str","^Search the room more thoroughly for anything personal.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":4},"ev","str","^Leave the body for the guard and return to the main hall.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-1","flg":4},{"c-0":["\n",{"->":"q1_find_mila_locket"},{"#f":5}],"c-1":["\n",{"->":"q1_investigation_hub"},{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"q1_find_mila_locket":["ev",{"VAR?":"q1_mila_locket_found"},"!","/ev",[{"->":".^.b","c":true},{"b":["\n","ev",true,"/ev",{"VAR=":"q1_mila_locket_found","re":true},"ev",true,"/ev",{"VAR=":"has_mila_locket","re":true},"^You run your fingers along the edge of the tub, then under it. Nails catch on warped wood, a loose board. You pry it up.","\n","^Nestled in the damp cavity, wrapped in a strip of cloth, lies a small painted locket on a tarnished chain. One side shows a young woman in better days: hair smoothed, eyes bright, cheeks touched with careful color. The other bears a miniature of a cottage with a leaning birch and crooked fence.","\n","^\"Not yours,\" you murmur to the corpse. \"So who were you hiding it from?\"","\n","^You slip the locket away.","\n",{"->":"q1_investigation_hub"},{"->":".^.^.^.6"},null]}],[{"->":".^.b"},{"b":["\n","^You find nothing you haven't already seen.","\n",{"->":"q1_investigation_hub"},{"->":".^.^.^.6"},null]}],"nop","\n",{"#f":1}],"q1_tomas_neyman":[["ev",true,"/ev",{"VAR=":"q1_spoke_to_neyman","re":true},"^The inn room stinks of boiled linen and ointment. Tomas Neyman lies on his stomach on a pallet, bandages wrapped from navel to mid-thigh. Sweat beads on his shaved scalp. A camp surgeon hovers nearby, hands stained with salve.","\n","^Neyman grits his teeth when he sees you.","\n","^\"Come to gawk, witcher? Or to tell me I'm cursed?\"","\n","^\"Depends what you tell me,\" you say. \"You were in a private tub. Water went from warm to boiling.\"","\n","^He barks a humorless laugh that collapses into a hiss of pain.","\n","^\"Sat there like a lord,\" he wheezes. \"Room to myself. Water just right. Next breath it roared like a kettle and—\"","\n","^He bites off the memory, knuckles white on the mattress.","\n","^\"Nobody touched the valves,\" the surgeon mutters. \"Oszkar says the pipes were sound.\"","\n","^You move closer. \"Heard anything? Felt anything?\"","\n","^\"Just heat.\" Neyman stares at the wall. \"And...hands. Like someone pushing my head down. Couldn't see a bloody thing.\"","\n","^You nod at the folded note on the table, stamped with the baths' seal.","\n","^\"Private bath's quite a benefit for a soldier. Nilfgaard must be doing well in the war.\"","\n","^\"Karol Wenda,\" Neyman says. \"Quartermaster handled officers' comforts. You wanted a quiet soak on nights the captain clears the baths, you went through him. Or through that attendant, if you liked a softer voice.\"","\n","^He swallows.","\n","^\"First night like that, I thought I'd fallen into a noble's lap. Whole baths to ourselves. Captain didn't like locals hearing him shout.\"","\n","^\"Shouting at who?\"","\n","^\"Girls from town, usually. He favored one, though.\" Neyman glances at the surgeon, then away. \"Laundress. Pretty. Pregnant. Didn't stay long.\"","\n","^The surgeon snorts softly.","\n","^\"Show me the burns,\" you say.","\n","^Neyman tenses, but nods. The surgeon peels back the linen. The burns climb in angry red bands, worst where the water would have swirled between his legs. Flesh there is mottled and raw.","\n","^\"The water boiled hardest there,\" the surgeon mutters. \"Though I don't know how that's possible.\"","\n","^Patterns. Scalding where a man takes his pleasure. Strangling with a towel. A brazier crushing a stomach.","\n","ev",{"VAR?":"q1_spoke_to_lida"},{"VAR?":"q1_identified_bannik"},"!","&&","/ev",[{"->":".^.b","c":true},{"b":["\n","ev",true,"/ev",{"VAR=":"q1_identified_bannik","re":true},{"->":".^.^.^.55"},null]}],"nop","\n","ev","str","^Ask about the captain's 'cleared' nights before you leave.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":4},"ev","str","^Say nothing more. You've heard enough.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-1","flg":4},{"c-0":["\n","^Neyman shifts, grimacing.","\n","^\"Captain Janrek liked things...quiet,\" he says. \"Cleared the baths, paid extra. One night, owner argued. Said that's not what the baths were for. Captain told him war changes what every place is for.\"","\n",{"->":"q1_investigation_hub"},{"#f":5}],"c-1":["\n",{"->":"q1_investigation_hub"},{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"q1_lida_sarnova":[["ev",true,"/ev",{"VAR=":"q1_spoke_to_lida","re":true},"^Lida's cottage sits two lanes away. Inside, the air smells of stale steam and boiled cabbage. She lies propped on pillows, scarf wrapped high on her neck. Bruises seep yellow and purple beneath the cloth.","\n","^She manages a rasp of a greeting when she sees the medallion.","\n","^\"Oszkar sent you,\" she whispers. \"About the...accident. That's what he calls it, anyhow.\"","\n","^\"Three accidents,\" you correct. \"Tell me about yours.\"","\n","^She brings a shaking hand to her throat.","\n","^\"I was alone. A private room. Just me and my work. Door was shut but not bolted. I was straightening linens, thinking about nothing much.\" Her fingers curl as if remembering cloth. \"Then a towel snapped tight round my neck from behind. Hard. Barely time to scream.\"","\n","^You picture it: linen twisting like a noose.","\n","^\"I clawed at it,\" she says. \"Felt...cold fingers under the cloth. Long. Like bones wrapped in wet paper.\"","\n","^Her eyes unfocus, pupils shrinking.","\n","^\"Then something else. On my back. Nails tracing down my spine. Like it was...searching. Looking under my skin for something.\"","\n","^She shudders.","\n","^\"Another girl heard me choking. Kicked the door in, thankfully. Towel went slack, and I hit the floor.\"","\n","^\"Let me see your back,\" you say.","\n","^The request freezes her. Shame, fear, habit fight in her face. Then she nods, slow.","\n","^The bruises on her throat are bad. The scars on her back are worse. Fresh, healing, a lattice of curved lines from nape to lower spine. Not claw-marks from a wild strike. Deliberate. Patterns written in flesh.","\n","^Spirits that haunt baths. Spirits that strangle attendants who look away. Spirits that trace fortunes in scratches down the spine.","\n","^\"Bannik,\" you mutter.","\n","^Lida tenses. \"Is that a curse?\"","\n","^\"Guardian. Liminal places. Places of rest, like baths.\" You straighten. \"Punishes those who foul its house.\"","\n","^\"Punishes? But I-\" Her voice frays as her mind anchors to a memory, one that has haunted her. \"I-I saw blood on the towels, once. This-this pregant girl went in, and then sometime later Oszkar was mopping up blood. Too much for an accident. Too much for a birth. Never saw the girl leave, but that Captain Janrek must've. Leave, that is. Oszkar said it wasn't something for me to worry about. Said I should forget.\"","\n","^\"You didn't report it.\"","\n","^\"I...\" Her gaze drops to her hands. \"War. Officers. What could I do? My mop's no sword, witcher.\"","\n","^She swallows.","\n","^\"You want the truth, ask Agata. She was the midwife. She was there that night. Soldiers took her after, though. For 'protection.'\" Lida laughs, a small, bitter sound. \"No one's seen her since. She's at that camp of theirs. I'm sure of it.\"","\n","ev",true,"/ev",{"VAR=":"q1_identified_bannik","re":true},"ev","str","^Reassure Lida as best you can and leave.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":4},"ev","str","^Press her once more about what she saw that night.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-1","flg":4},{"c-0":["\n","^\"Won't stop it coming back,\" she says, staring at the ceiling. \"But maybe I'll say something, next time.\"","\n",{"->":"q1_investigation_hub"},{"#f":5}],"c-1":["\n","^She squeezes her eyes shut.","\n","^\"Blood on tiles,\" she whispers. \"Too much for mother and child both. Oszkar shouting that this isn't what the baths are for. Quartermaster Wenda saying they'd be gone before dawn. I closed the door and tried to forget the smell. Smelled like death.\"","\n",{"->":"q1_investigation_hub"},{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"q1_identify_bannik":["^You lean against a damp stone wall, listening to the baths breathe. Steam sighs through pipes. Water clatters in basins. Someone laughs nervously, too loud.","\n","^Scalding water at the groin. A towel that strangles on its own. A brazier hurled with malice, crushing the part of a man that's fed another life. Scratches down a spine, careful and curved.","\n","^Not a random haunting. Not a mindless wraith.","\n","^\"Bannik,\" you say aloud. \"Bath spirit. Reads futures on wet stone and bare backs. Punishes when its house is profaned.\"","\n","^You tuck the coarse white hair from the soldier's room into a pouch.","\n","^Now the question isn't _what_. It's _why_.","\n",{"->":"q1_investigation_hub"},{"#f":1}],"q1_midwife_path_entry":["ev",true,"/ev",{"VAR=":"agata_met","re":true},"ev",true,"/ev",{"VAR=":"agata_alive","re":true},"^The Nilfgaardian camp huddles a short ride from Stonecross, lines of black canvas and muddy trenches marching up the hill. Smoke from cookfires mixes with the sour reek of latrines and oiled leather.","\n","^Soldiers eye your medallion and swords with open dislike, hands near hilts, and even though no one stands in your way, it seems few care to assist when you ask for the \"midwife.\"","\n","^\"Old woman from the baths?\" one says finally. \"They stuck her in the infirmary. Said she was hysterical.\"","\n","^He jerks his chin toward a tent marked with a stitched white sun.","\n",{"->":"q1_midwife_testimony"},{"#f":1}],"q1_midwife_testimony":["ev",true,"/ev",{"VAR=":"q1_spoke_to_agata","re":true},"^Inside, the infirmary tent is a graveyard of cots and damp linen. Agata sits on the edge of one, hands folded in her lap. Her hair is a white cloud pinned held back with cheap ribbon. Her eyes are red-rimmed but clear.","\n","^She looks up when you approach.","\n","^\"So the rumors are true,\" she says. \"I hear little in this tent, confined as I am, but I heard about Wenda. Whispers of his death are cutting like a hot knife through this camp. But a witcher...\"","\n","^You sit on a low stool opposite.","\n","^\"Tell me about the girl,\" you say curtly. \"The night she gave birth in baths.\"","\n","^Agata flinches, surprised. Then exhales.","\n","^\"I see. Mila from Rybnik. The laundress. Pretty, until the captain took a liking to her.\" Her mouth twists.","\n","^\"They brought her in after dark. Captain Janrek, quartermaster Wenda. The baths were cleared, staff turned away. Oszkar said it was...a matter of discretion. She was near to bursting, poor girl. Baby came hard, but alive, healthy, screaming—good sign, that is. Little thing wanted the world to hear...\"","\n","^Agata's gaze grows distant.","\n","^\"Mila wanted the world to hear, too. Told the captain he'd acknowledge the child, or she'd scream to every tavern on the Pontar about how she got it. He...\"","\n","^Agata's voice fails. She swallows.","\n","^\"He didn't touch her. Not directly. Stood there, eyes like glass, and told Wenda to 'handle it.' Quartermaster grabbed a towel. Pressed it over her mouth. She fought. Her second fight of the night, she hadn't the strength left. Blood on tiles, water everywhere. When it was done...\"","\n","^She presses a hand to her chest.","\n","^\"Oszkar helped them shift the body before dawn,\" she says. \"Wrapped her in sheets, carried her out like dirty laundry. I washed the blood. They told me if I spoke, I'd not be long for the world. Next day, soldiers came. Said I'd be 'safer' with the garrison.\"","\n","^Her laugh is brittle.","\n","^\"Haven't seen the child since. Maybe someone with more spine took her away.\"","\n","^You rise.","\n","^\"By keeping your mouth shut,\" you say, \"you've damned others.\"","\n","^\"I know.\" Agata's eyes film. \"I've known every night since they brought me here. I feel for Lida. God's only know why she's wrapped up in this. But those others, witcher...Wenda, Neyman...I'm not sure I can muster up the pity.\"","\n",{"->":"q1_investigation_hub"},{"#f":1}],"q1_bannik_confrontation_entry":[["ev",false,"/ev",{"VAR=":"bannik_encountered","re":true},"^You return to Oszkar.","\n","^\"The baths need clearing,\" you say. \"Staff out, patrons out. Lock the outer door.\"","\n","^He blanches. \"You...found something.\"","\n","^\"Found enough.\"","\n","^He chews his lip, but nods. Bells are rung. Grumbling soldiers and locals shuffle into the street, clutching towels to chests, muttering about refunds and curses. Oszkar bars the door behind them, leaving only lanterns and the sound of water.","\n","^\"You sure about this, witcher?\"","\n","^You loosen the sword strap across your chest. \"Certainty's for priests.\"","\n","^Two ways to meet a bath spirit. One invites talk. The other invites burns.","\n","ev","str","^Keep armor and steel on, walk in armed.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":4},"ev","str","^Strip down to a towel. Meet a bath spirit on its own terms.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-1","flg":4},{"c-0":["\n",{"->":"q1_bannik_armed_approach"},{"#f":5}],"c-1":["\n","^You leave steel and leather on a peg by the door. The room feels wrong without their weight.","\n",{"->":"q1_bannik_towel_approach"},{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"q1_bannik_armed_approach":["ev",true,"/ev",{"VAR=":"q1_bannik_approach_armed","re":true},"^You step into the main hall in full gear. Steam curls around mail and leather. Your boots squeak on wet tile. The temperature rises with every step. Heat presses under your breastplate like a hand. Sweat crawls down your neck. The medallion at your throat trembles. Pipes groan. A brazier chain rattles overhead without wind.","\n","^\"Don't like guests in plate, do you?\" you mutter.","\n","^You unbuckle your sword belt but keep the blade in hand. A laugh rasps out of the pipes. Dry. Old. Too close.","\n","^From somewhere in the steam: \"War-boots in my water. Iron stink. Like a barracks, again.\"","\n","^The doors shudder. A shutter slams hard enough to spit splinters. Steam thickens—white, choking, alive.","\n",{"->":"q1_bannik_armed_skirmish"},{"#f":1}],"q1_bannik_armed_skirmish":[["^The heat swells under your armor. A thin jet of boiling water snaps across the tiles like a whip. You pivot, too slow. The steam hides the thing until it wants you to see it: a hunched shape, beard dragging, skin like wet ash, eyes like coals. It darts in and out of the vapor, slapping shutters, toppling buckets, flinging ladles like stones.","\n","^The plates on your shoulders bite hot. Not burning yet. Warning. A second burst of steam hits you low. Your knees want to buckle. Now it’s pain. The slow pain of heat trapped where you can’t shed it. The bannik’s laugh scrapes your ears.","\n","^Bannik: \"Cook inside your shell, then.\"","\n","ev","str","^Keep fighting. End it the hard way.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":4},"ev","str","^Enough. Strip the iron off and try talking.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-1","flg":4},{"c-0":["\n",{"->":"q1_bannik_armed_fight_commit"},{"#f":5}],"c-1":["\n",{"->":"q1_bannik_strip_to_talk"},{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"q1_bannik_armed_fight_commit":["^You set your stance, blade low, eyes narrowed. If it wants war in its house, it’ll get it.","\n","^The bannik comes in fast—too fast for something that looks half-dead. A claw hooks your ribs. Hot pain blooms. The kind that stays.","\n",{"->":"q1_bannik_fight_loop"},{"#f":1}],"q1_bannik_strip_to_talk":["^You strip, hands moving fast. Buckles, straps, leather stuck to sweat. You drop it all like there's a stuffed unicorn in the room. The heat eases the moment metal leaves your skin. You take a towel—more insult than cover—and walk back into the steam with empty hands.","\n",{"->":"q1_bannik_towel_approach"},{"#f":1}],"q1_bannik_towel_approach":["ev",false,"/ev",{"VAR=":"q1_bannik_approach_armed","re":true},"^A towel around your waist, medallion still at your throat, you pad barefoot across warm stone. Steam beads on scarred skin. Old burns ache in sympathy. You pick a tub in the center of the hall, sit, and sink into the heat. Close your eyes.","\n","^\"House is cleared,\" you say quietly. \"Just you and me.\"","\n","^Water laps. Pipes creak.","\n",{"->":"q1_bannik_dialogue_scene"},{"#f":1}],"q1_bannik_dialogue_scene":[["ev",true,"/ev",{"VAR=":"bannik_encountered","re":true},"ev",true,"/ev",{"VAR=":"q1_spoke_to_bannik","re":true},"ev",true,"/ev",{"VAR=":"bannik_pause_granted","re":true},"^For a time, nothing happens. Just the sound of water, your own breathing, the faint hiss of your medallion. Then the steam thickens, drawing tight around you. The lanterns dim to candle-flames. Something moves across the surface of the water opposite you without making a ripple.","\n","^When it clears, he sits there.","\n","^Small. Hunched. Skin like old wax, wrinkled and gray-blue from centuries of soaking. Beard and hair long enough to pool in the water, hiding the rest of him. Eyes like two little coals, watching you from under a thatch of filthy hair.","\n","^The bannik.","\n","^\"You sit,\" it rasps. Its voice sounds like water forced through too-narrow pipes. \"Better without your shell on. You clank when you bring steel into the steam.\" It chuckles, a sound like hot stones grinding.","\n","^\"I read the girl's back,\" it says. \"Found the future under her skin. The world yet unwritten. Saw you here, white hair. Yellow eyes in my house.\"","\n","^It reaches one long, veined hand out of the water and trails blackened nails along its own spine, miming.","\n","^\"Saw my own end, too. Not in this tub. Not yet.\"","\n","^\"You killed Wenda,\" you say. \"Boiled Neyman. Throttled Lida.\"","\n","^It tilts its head.","\n","^\"I punished,\" it whispers, correcting you. \"They profaned the water. Rules broken. Birth to murder. They brought a girl swollen with life into my steam, and then took life. Lied. Covered her with towels. Washed her blood down my throat.\"","\n","^The tiles shudder under you. It lifts a dripping finger, counts them off.","\n","^\"I see roles,\" it says. \"Not names. One who arranged beds and favors. One who enjoyed blood-bought privilege. One who saw and chose silence. One who killed. One who let him.\"","\n","^\"Neyman, Wenda, Lida, Oszkar,\" you say. \"Captain Janrek.\"","\n","^\"Words,\" it shrugs. \"Meat in tubs. They will learn. I have seen it. But futures can be scrubbed.\"","\n","^Its last words were pointed. It peers at you. It wants to bargain.","\n","^\"I want one more weight in this water,\" it says. \"The man who thought guilt washed clean in my steam. Or the one who sold his house for coin and closed his eyes. Captain. Owner. Bring one. Maybe both. Or I start taking others. Everyone plays a role at some time.\"","\n","ev","str","^Challenge its right to punish those who were afraid more than guilty.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":4},"ev","str","^Agree that Wenda and the captain deserve worse. Press it about limits.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-1","flg":4},"ev","str","^Keep your tone neutral. Ask it to stay its hand while you settle matters with the living.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-2","flg":4},{"c-0":["^ ","\n","^\"You boiled Neyman,\" you say. \"He arranged baths. Took advantage of his rank, yes. But he didn't kill anyone.\"","\n","^\"That does not clean him,\" the bannik hisses. \"He drank from the same basin. Smiled while they scraped blood from tiles. Sat in water bought with her breath. Fear is no soap.\"","\n","^\"You strangled Lida. She looked away because she'd be next if she spoke.\"","\n","^\"Silence is a choice,\" it says mildly. \"So is screaming and raging. She chose. I chose.\"","\n",{"->":"q1_bannik_options"},{"#f":5}],"c-1":["\n","^\"Quartermaster killed her,\" you say. \"Not you.\"","\n","^\"On command,\" the bannik replies. \"Like a knife in the hand.\"","\n","^Its eyes brighten.","\n","^\"Captain thought if he never touched her, his hands stayed clean. He is wrong. Water remembers. I remember.\"","\n",{"->":"q1_bannik_options"},{"#f":5}],"c-2":["\n","^\"You've seen futures,\" you say. \"See this one. I deal with the captain and Oszkar. You stay in your tubs. No more stranglings. No more boiling baths.\"","\n","^It considers. Water swirls around its beard without moving its arms.","\n","^\"I see...fog,\" it admits. \"Steam that hangs without rising. I might wait. For a time. Not long, witcher.\"","\n",{"->":"q1_bannik_options"},{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"q1_bannik_options":[["^The bannik sinks a little deeper, only eyes and hair above water.","\n","^\"So, witcher,\" it murmurs. \"Will you crack the kettle or throw in more bones?\"","\n","ev","str","^Attack the bannik now. End the hauntings by killing the spirit.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":4},"ev","str","^Promise to bring Oszkar as payment.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-1","flg":4},"ev","str","^Promise to bring Captain Janrek for judgment.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-2","flg":4},"ev","str","^Refuse to feed it anyone. Insist on human justice only.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-3","flg":4},{"c-0":["\n",{"->":"q1_bannik_tub_kill_choice"},{"#f":5}],"c-1":["\n","^\"The owner profaned you,\" you say. \"Let him be the end it.\"","\n","^The bannik's teeth show in something like a smile.","\n","^\"Bring him,\" it whispers. \"Lock the door. Leave. I will do the rest.\"","\n",{"->":"q1_after_bannik_promise"},{"#f":5}],"c-2":["\n","^\"You want the captain,\" you say. \"You'll have him. Might take time.\"","\n","^Its eyes flare.","\n","^\"Time I have,\" it says. \"Bodies rot. Stone does not.\"","\n",{"->":"q1_after_bannik_promise"},{"#f":5}],"c-3":["\n","^\"You don't get to pick human offerings,\" you say. \"Not while I'm here. I'll find justice for those who deserve it.\"","\n","^The bannik's expression curdles.","\n","^\"Then you better be a very good butcher, witcher,\" it rasps. \"Or I go back to choosing for you.\"","\n","ev",false,"/ev",{"VAR=":"bannik_pause_granted","re":true},{"->":"q1_after_bannik_promise"},{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"q1_after_bannik_promise":["^Steam thins. The bannik's shape blurs, then unravels into mist. The halls feel emptier. No less damp. You climb out of the tub, skin prickling from the heat. Whatever you decide about Oszkar and Janrek, the bath spirit will remember.","\n",{"->":"q1_investigation_hub"},{"#f":1}],"q1_bannik_tub_kill_choice":[["^You shift in the tub, water sloshing against the tile. The bannik watches without blinking. It looks... pleased. Like it’s been waiting for you to flinch.","\n","^Bannik: \"Witcher thinks he can wash judgment in my water. Try, then.\"","\n","^You don’t reach for a sword. You left it by the door. Just steam. Stone. Water. And your hands.","\n","ev","str","^Use Signs. Make the bathhouse itself kill it.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":4},"ev","str","^Hold. Don't start this naked.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-1","flg":4},{"c-0":["\n",{"->":"q1_bannik_tub_fight_signs"},{"#f":5}],"c-1":["\n",{"->":"q1_bannik_options"},{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"q1_bannik_tub_fight_signs":["^You slide out of the tub in one motion, towel dragging, feet finding purchase on slick stone. Your medallion hums low.","\n","^You attempt to draw a Sign in the wet air. The bannik comes in fast—too fast for something that looks half-dead. A claw hooks your ribs. Hot pain blooms. The kind that stays.","\n",{"->":"q1_bannik_fight_loop"},{"#f":1}],"q1_bannik_fight_loop":[["^You answer with a Sign, palms stinging from the force.","\n","ev","str","^Aard. Break its footing and the room with it.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":20},"ev","str","^Igni. Burn the steam away long enough to see.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-1","flg":20},"ev","str","^Yrden. Trap it on the tiles.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-2","flg":20},{"c-0":["\n",{"->":"q1_bannik_tub_aard"},{"#f":5}],"c-1":["^ ","\n",{"->":"q1_bannik_tub_igni"},{"#f":5}],"c-2":["\n",{"->":"q1_bannik_tub_yrden"},{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"q1_bannik_tub_yrden":[["^You carve Yrden into the stone with two fingers, the glyph biting cold into heat. Purple lines crawl over wet tile like cracks in ice. The bannik steps in, and the air changes.","\n","^Its movement turns thick, as if it’s wading through tar. It shrieks, not in pain. More like offense.","\n","^Bannik: \"Old marks. Old rules.\"","\n","^It still reaches you. Slow now, but strong. A hand clamps your throat. Nails dig in. Your vision spots at the edges.","\n","ev","str","^Drive it deeper into the circle. Finish it here.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":4},"ev","str","^Break away and try your sword.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-1","flg":4},{"c-0":["\n",{"->":"q1_bannik_finish"},{"#f":5}],"c-1":["\n","^You cast Aard to push it back and scramble for your blade.","\n",{"->":"q1_bannik_fight"},{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"q1_bannik_tub_aard":["^You pull air into your chest, then shove it out with the Sign. Aard hits like a hammer. Steam blasts apart. Shutters slam open. The brazier clatters, half-topples, hangs for a breath—then crashes down, cracking tile.","\n","^The bannik skids, skin scraping stone. It laughs even then, wet and ugly. It lunges again. Closer now, furious.","\n",{"->":"q1_bannik_fight_loop"},{"#f":1}],"q1_bannik_tub_igni":["^A thin line of fire snaps from your fingers. Not to burn it, yet, but to clear the veil. The steam recoils, thinning for a heartbeat. You see it properly: the beard like drowned rope, the eye fixed on your throat.","\n","^It darts in anyway, using the last of the vapor like a curtain. ","ev",{"VAR?":"q1_bannik_approach_armed"},"/ev",[{"->":".^.b","c":true},{"b":["^ Its claw opens your shoulder and you drop your sword.",{"->":".^.^.^.7"},null]}],"nop","^ ","ev",{"VAR?":"q1_bannik_approach_armed"},"!","/ev",[{"->":".^.b","c":true},{"b":["^ Its claw opens your shoulder.",{"->":".^.^.^.14"},null]}],"nop","^ Blood runs hot down your arm.","\n","^No sword. No reach. Just you and it, breathing the same hot air.","\n",{"->":"q1_bannik_fight_loop"},{"#f":1}],"q1_bannik_fight":["^Steel flashes, scattering drops of scalding water across tile.","\n","^The spirit hisses, vanishing into steam. Lanterns explode in showers of sparks as invisible hands bat them aside. Jets of boiling water blast from cracked pipes, searing exposed skin.","\n","^You work through it. Signs crack the air—Aard to blow steam aside, Yrden to slow the thing when it flickers into sight, Igni to turn its own heat against it.","\n","^At last your blade bites something that isn't mist. The bannik screams, voice like a kettle left too long on the fire, then goes silent. Water sluices back into baths. The heat drops to merely uncomfortable.","\n","^Your medallion calms.","\n","ev",false,"/ev",{"VAR=":"bannik_alive","re":true},"ev",true,"/ev",{"VAR=":"bannik_encountered","re":true},"ev",false,"/ev",{"VAR=":"bannik_pause_granted","re":true},"^You wipe the blade on a towel, wondering if you've just freed the baths—or cut the only judge willing to touch what the law won't.","\n",{"->":"q1_resolution_hub"},{"#f":1}],"q1_bannik_finish":["^Your throat burns. Your hands fumble, slick with sweat and bathwater. You shove the bannik’s weight back into Yrden’s biting lines. It fights like a feral thing.","\n","^Then you do what you’re good at: you use your environment. You slam your palm to the brazier chain and draw a Sign again: Aard, but focused. Precise.","\n","^The chain snaps taut. The brazier swings wide and heavy through the steamy air. The bannik tries to slip away. Yrden drags at it like mud. The iron edge takes it across the spine with a sound like wet wood cracking.","\n","^For a heartbeat, it’s pinned—half under iron, half in the circle—and you drive your knee down onto its throat, forearm across its jaw. It thrashes. Nails rake your neck.","\n","^Your medallion hums louder.","\n","^You sign Igni, focusing flame into the hollows of its eyes. You persist until the coals cinder and turn small. Then smaller. Then still. The steam doesn’t stop at once. It just... frays.","\n","ev",false,"/ev",{"VAR=":"bannik_alive","re":true},"ev",true,"/ev",{"VAR=":"bannik_encountered","re":true},"ev",false,"/ev",{"VAR=":"bannik_pause_granted","re":true},"^You sit back on the tiles, breathing hard. Closer than it should’ve been.","\n","^But done.","\n",{"->":"q1_resolution_hub"},{"#f":1}],"q1_confront_oszkar":[["ev",true,"/ev",{"VAR=":"q1_oszkar_confronted","re":true},"^You find Oszkar alone in his office, ear pressed to the wall as if he's trying to hear something in the stone. He jerks upright when you enter.","\n","^\"Well?\" he blurts. \"You...took care of it?\"","\n","^\"You ever see a bath spirit?\" you ask.","\n","^He pales. \"Folk tales. Old wives' nonsense.\"","\n","^\"It read Lida's back like a ledger,\" you say. \"Knows every crime in these tiles. Knows you cleared the house for a secret birth. Knows you watched a girl die on your floor.\"","\n","^His hands tremble on the edge of the desk.","\n","^\"I didn't kill anyone,\" he whispers. \"Captain gave orders. Soldiers obeyed. I...kept the water hot. That's all.\"","\n","^\"You locked the doors,\" you say. \"Turned staff away. Helped move the body.\"","\n","^He squeezes his eyes shut.","\n","^\"It's war,\" he grumbles fiercely, as if no ones seems to understand him. \"Officers do as they please. If I'd refused, they'd have hung me from the rafters and burned the baths besides.\"","\n","ev","str","^Push him towards confession. Make him feel the weight of what he did.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":4},"ev","str","^Stay cold. Focus on options, not his guilt.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-1","flg":4},{"c-0":["\n","^\"Maybe you should save them the effort. You kept your baths,\" you say. \"Mila lost her life. Child lost its mother.\"","\n","^His shoulders hunch.","\n","^\"I hear her sometimes,\" he says, voice ragged. \"In the pipes. In the drains. I scrubbed and scrubbed. Blood never quite left the grout.\"","\n",{"->":"q1_confront_oszkar_choice"},{"#f":5}],"c-1":["\n","^\"Whether you feel bad doesn't interest me,\" you say. \"What you do next does.\"","\n","^He flinches as if struck.","\n",{"->":"q1_confront_oszkar_choice"},{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"q1_confront_oszkar_choice":[["^Oszkar licks dry lips.","\n","^\"So what now, witcher? You turn me over to the guard? To the captain? To...whatever is in my baths?\"","\n","ev","str","^Threaten to hand him to Nilfgaardian authority unless he comes clean.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":4},"ev","str","^Hint that there is a way for him to 'cleanse' the baths, by offering himself to the bannik.","/str",{"VAR?":"bannik_alive"},"/ev",{"*":".^.c-1","flg":5},"ev","str","^Tell him you'll leave him to live under the bannik's shadow—for now.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-2","flg":4},{"c-0":["\n","^\"You helped cover a murder,\" you say. \"Turn yourself in, or I walk to the camp and tell your captain how you let his secret out.\"","\n","^He stares at you, then at his own damp hands.","\n","^\"Nilfgaard doesn't care about village girls,\" he whispers. \"They care about discipline. Image. If I talk, they hang me. If I don't, that thing in the water does.\"","\n","^He gives a broken laugh.","\n","^\"Suppose that's justice.\"","\n",{"->":"q1_confront_oszkar_outcome"},{"#f":5}],"c-1":["\n","^\"Spirit wants a weight,\" you say. \"Yours or the captain's. Walk into a tub alone, it might call it square.\"","\n","^His face drains of blood.","\n","^\"You asking me to drown myself?\" he croaks.","\n","^\"Not asking,\" you say. \"Laying out options.\"","\n","^He grips the desk until his knuckles whiten. The guilt has been weighing heavy on him for some time.","\n","^\"Come back...tonight,\" he mutters. \"When the girls are gone. I'll...decide.\"","\n",{"->":"q1_confront_oszkar_outcome"},{"#f":5}],"c-2":["\n","^\"You sleep in this house,\" you say. \"Share its hauntings. Its new reputation. Maybe that's punishment enough.\"","\n","^He lets out a breath halfway between relief and dread.","\n","^\"You have a cruel sense of mercy, witcher.\"","\n",{"->":"q1_confront_oszkar_outcome"},{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"q1_confront_oszkar_outcome":["^Whatever he chooses, you leave him with his ledgers and ghosts.","\n",{"->":"q1_investigation_hub"},{"#f":1}],"q1_oszkar_to_bannik":["ev",{"VAR?":"bannik_alive"},{"VAR?":"oszkar_alive"},"&&","/ev",[{"->":".^.b","c":true},{"b":["\n","ev",false,"/ev",{"VAR=":"oszkar_alive","re":true},"ev",true,"/ev",{"VAR=":"oszkar_given_to_bannik","re":true},"ev",true,"/ev",{"VAR=":"bannik_pause_granted","re":true},"^That night, Oszkar meets you in the main hall, eyes hollow, towel clutched in white-knuckled hands.","\n","^\"Do it quick,\" he mutters. \"Lock the door. If...if it stops with me, maybe that's...\"","\n","^He trails off.","\n","^You close the bolts. Lanterns dim as he steps into the water, alone. Steam thickens, swallowing his thin shoulders, his shaking hands. The last thing you see is his face when something unseen grips his ankle and pulls. You don't watch the rest. You stand by the door until the screaming stops and the water goes still. When you open it again, the tub is empty. Only a few gray hairs cling to the lip. The pipes hum, content.","\n",{"->":".^.^.^.6"},null]}],"nop","\n",{"->":"q1_resolution_hub"},{"#f":1}],"q1_resolution_hub":[["^Steam curls lazily through the quiet baths. No strangled gasps. No distant boiling roar. Just water, stone, and the wet echo of your own footsteps.","\n","^You've encountered the bannik. Dragged the truth out of either Agata or Oszkar, or both. You know who ordered Mila's death and who carried it out.","\n","^Now comes the part contracts never write down: what you do with all of that.","\n","ev",{"VAR?":"bannik_alive"},{"VAR?":"oszkar_given_to_bannik"},"!","&&","/ev",[{"->":".^.b","c":true},{"b":["\n","ev","str","^Deliver Oszkar to the bannik. Feed the bathhouse its owner.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":4},{"->":".^.^.^.13"},{"c-0":["^ ","\n",{"->":"q1_oszkar_to_bannik"},{"#f":5}]}]}],"nop","\n","ev",{"VAR?":"bannik_alive"},"/ev",[{"->":".^.b","c":true},{"b":["\n","ev","str","^Leave the bannik in place as a grim guardian for now. Focus on Janrek.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":4},{"->":".^.^.^.19"},{"c-0":["\n",{"->":"q1_resolution_human_justice"},{"#f":5}]}]}],"nop","\n","ev",{"VAR?":"bannik_alive"},"!","/ev",[{"->":".^.b","c":true},{"b":["\n","ev","str","^With the bannik dead, see to human justice alone.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":4},{"->":".^.^.^.26"},{"c-0":["\n",{"->":"q1_resolution_human_justice"},{"#f":5}]}]}],"nop","\n","ev","str","^Decide the contract's done. Take your coin and leave Stonecross to its ghosts.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":4},{"c-0":["\n","^You count your crowns and leave the baths to the river fog and the war.","\n",{"->":"q1_mark_complete"},{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"q1_resolution_human_justice":["^You stand outside of the bathhouse, watching black cloaks snap in the wind as a patrol walks through town towards the garrison camp. Who you assume to be Captain Janrek Olshanski holds the lead of the patrol, cloak pinned with polished sun-badges.","\n","^He looks you over like a piece of equipment. Useful. Replaceable.","\n","^Oszkar's confession and Agata's testimony burn in your pocket like coals. You could present them to a Nilfgaardian magistrate, if one can be found. Or seek your own justice against the captain, let the war sort out the rest.","\n","^In the end, you do what you always do: choose one road and walk it, knowing the others will still exist somewhere, in some other choices. Perhaps in one of them, you take Janrek's head here and now, but in this telling, something stills your blade. For now.","\n",{"->":"q1_mark_complete"},{"#f":1}],"q1_mark_complete":["ev",true,"/ev",{"VAR=":"Q1_COMPLETED","re":true},"^You leave Stonecross behind. Steam thins in the cold river wind. Behind you, baths still breathe, quieter now, but never clean. You head for the Nilfgaardian garrison camp.","\n",{"->":"q2_flowers_on_old_blood_entry"},{"#f":1}],"q2_flowers_on_old_blood_entry":["ev",false,"/ev",{"VAR=":"Q2_COMPLETED","re":true},"ev",{"VAR?":"agata_met"},"/ev",[{"->":".^.b","c":true},{"b":["\n","ev",true,"/ev",{"VAR=":"q2_entry_from_agata","re":true},{"->":"q2_entry_met_agata"},{"->":".^.^.^.9"},null]}],[{"->":".^.b"},{"b":["\n","ev",false,"/ev",{"VAR=":"q2_entry_from_agata","re":true},{"->":"q2_entry_never_met_agata"},{"->":".^.^.^.9"},null]}],"nop","\n",{"#f":1}],"q2_entry_met_agata":[["^You haven't gone far from Stonecross when a girl in a garrison apron all but runs into Roach's nose. She skids to a halt, cheeks flushed, hands twisting in her skirt.","\n","^\"Witcher?\" she gasps. \"You—you came to the camp before. Spoke with Agata. The midwife.\"","\n","^You nod.","\n","^\"They found her,\" the girl says. \"Outside camp. In the flowers. Throat cut. Sergeant Corvin with her, torn to bits. And...\"","\n","^She swallows.","\n","^\"Flowers growing out of them,\" she whispers. \"Red ones. Officers say it's a beast in the camp. Says he'll pay for a witcher.\"","\n","^She looks up at you, eyes too old for her face.","\n","^\"Will you look?\"","\n","ev","str","^Agree to go with her to Widow's Field.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":4},"ev","str","^Ask a few quick questions before you ride.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-1","flg":4},{"c-0":["\n","^\"Name?\" you ask.","\n","^\"Zosia,\" she says. \"Zosia Drozd.\"","\n","^\"Lead on, Zosia.\"","\n",{"->":"q2_widows_field_bodies"},{"#f":5}],"c-1":["\n","^\"Who found them?\" you ask.","\n","^\"Scouts,\" she says. \"They came back pale as tallow. Said the flowers were...eating them.\"","\n","^She shakes her head.","\n","^\"Please. They'll move the bodies soon. Captain doesn't like reminders.\"","\n",{"->":"q2_widows_field_bodies"},{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"q2_entry_never_met_agata":[["^The garrison camp feels tighter than the ones you've been to before. Less shouting, more muttering. Men glance toward the flowered hill beyond the palisades and look away quickly.","\n","^At the gate, a kitchen maid with flour on her hands nearly drops her bucket when she sees you.","\n","^\"You the witcher Captain sent for?\" she asks. \"About the bodies in the field?\"","\n","^\"Bodies?\" you say. \"I'm here about a missing midwife. Agata.\"","\n","^She winces.","\n","^\"Then you're too late. But I can show you where she is. Where what's left of her is.\"","\n","^She wipes her hands on her apron.","\n","^\"Name's Zosia.\"","\n","ev","str","^Follow Zosia to Widow's Field.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":4},{"c-0":["\n",{"->":"q2_widows_field_bodies"},{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"q2_widows_field_bodies":[["ev",true,"/ev",{"VAR=":"q2_saw_bodies","re":true},"^Widow's Field looks almost pretty from a distance—gentle slope, a sea of dancing red petals. Up close, the flowers are ones you've not seen before. Petals thicker than poppies, stems studded with fine, backward-facing barbs.","\n","^In the densest patch lie two bodies.","\n","^Agata, the midwife, kneels with her forehead in the flowers, tongue gone, throat opened in one clean slice from ear to ear. Someone laid her carefully, almost reverently.","\n","^Sergeant Corvin—a decorated officer by the look of his uniform—sprawls half over her, armor peeled back, chest and arms scored with long, deliberate cuts. From every wound, flowers grow, red stems pushing in and out of meat, twining around bone.","\n","^Zosia stays well back, hand over her mouth.","\n","^\"They say a monster did it,\" she murmurs. \"Hiding somewhere in camp. Slit her and chewed on him.\"","\n","^You crouch and activate your Witcher Senses.","\n","^The flowers closest to the bodies are taller, thicker, glossier. Among them, petals lie half-chewed, spat out, stems crushed. Someone had been eating them.","\n","^You sniff a blossom. You smell only blood. Figures.","\n","^Boot prints: Agata's light steps beside heavier soldier's boots, up the hill. Two sets arrive. One set leaves. Later, the same heavier boots return alone, you deduce, overlapping their own trail. Here and there, in softer earth, you see the light impressions of a third set. Small, child-like.","\n","^\"Flowers've been chewed,\" you say to Zosia, looking for a reaction. She gives none.","\n","^\"Execution,\" you continue, glancing at Agata. \"Tongue first, then the throat.\"","\n","^That's no mystery to you. Last time you saw her, she was spilling the atrocities of Captain Janrek for all to hear. Perhaps, you think, you should've taken her with you that day. More than likely, you know, she would've told you no and ended up like this no matter what you did.","\n","^\"Corvin though,\" you go on, \"someone took their time. Long cuts, meant to bleed him slow.\"","\n","^Zosia hugs herself.","\n","^\"Captain says it's a creature,\" she whispers. \"Killed them both. Is that true?\"","\n","^\"No,\" you say, \"more than one monster is responsible for this.\"","\n","^You straighten.","\n","^\"Need to find out what these flowers are.\"","\n","ev","str","^Return with Zosia to camp. Listen to the mood in the tents.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":4},"ev","str","^Take a closer look at the tracks and flowers before leaving.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-1","flg":4},{"c-0":["\n",{"->":"q2_camp_hub"},{"#f":5}],"c-1":["\n",{"->":"q2_widows_field_more"},{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"q2_widows_field_more":["^You follow the heavy child-sized footprints as far as you can. They weave through the tallest flowers, vanish where stems are thickest, reappear where petals are smeared with fresh blood.","\n","^The trail ends at a patch where the flowers stand almost chest high, forming a subtle ring. Bones and bits of rusted metal hang low among the stems, disguised as windblown trash.","\n","^A den. But the thing that made it isn't here now.","\n","^You file its position away. You'll be back.","\n",{"->":"q2_camp_hub"},{"#f":1}],"q2_camp_hub":[["ev",{"VAR?":"q2_spoke_to_marta"},{"VAR?":"q2_spoke_to_janrek"},"||",{"VAR?":"q2_spoke_to_zosia"},"||","/ev",[{"->":".^.b","c":true},{"b":["\n","^What will you do now?","\n",{"->":".^.^.^.9"},null]}],[{"->":".^.b"},{"b":["\n","^The camp hums like a kicked hive. Men sharpen blades that don't need it, laugh too loud, drink too fast.","\n","^Snatches of talk follow you as you walk with Zosia.","\n","^\"Ever since that witcher stuck his nose in Stonecross,\" one soldier grumbles, \"bath nights dried up.\"","\n","^\"Oszkar says no more 'after-hours,'\" another mimics. \"Quartermaster that arranged 'em's dead. We wash like peasants now. No girls either.\"","\n","^\"Agata was mad anyhow,\" a third mutters. \"Best she's in the ground.\"","\n",{"->":".^.^.^.9"},null]}],"nop","\n","ev",{"VAR?":"q2_spoke_to_zosia"},"!","/ev",[{"->":".^.b","c":true},{"b":["\n","ev","str","^Ask Zosia to show you Agata's corner and Corvin's bunk.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":4},{"->":".^.^.^.16"},{"c-0":["\n",{"->":"q2_zosia_camp"},{"#f":5}]}]}],"nop","\n","ev",{"VAR?":"q2_spoke_to_janrek"},"!","/ev",[{"->":".^.b","c":true},{"b":["\n","ev","str","^Find Captain Janrek.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":4},{"->":".^.^.^.23"},{"c-0":["\n",{"->":"q2_janrek_first_meeting"},{"#f":5}]}]}],"nop","\n","ev",{"VAR?":"q2_spoke_to_zosia"},{"VAR?":"q2_spoke_to_janrek"},"||",{"VAR?":"q2_spoke_to_marta"},"!","&&","/ev",[{"->":".^.b","c":true},{"b":["\n","ev","str","^Follow Zosia's suggestion. Ride to Rybnik to see Marta, the herbalist.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":4},{"->":".^.^.^.34"},{"c-0":["\n",{"->":"q2_road_to_rybnik"},{"#f":5}]}]}],"nop","\n","ev",{"VAR?":"q2_spoke_to_marta"},{"VAR?":"q2_redcap_identified"},"&&","/ev",[{"->":".^.b","c":true},{"b":["\n","ev","str","^Return to Widow's Field to track the creature that chewed the flowers.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":4},{"->":".^.^.^.42"},{"c-0":["^ ","\n",{"->":"q2_track_redcap"},{"#f":5}]}]}],"nop","\n","ev","str","^Wander the camp a while longer, listening to loose tongues.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":4},{"c-0":["\n","^You hear more of the same: fear, blame, and men looking for something to stab so they don't have to think about orders.","\n",{"->":".^.^.^"},{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"q2_zosia_camp":["ev",true,"/ev",{"VAR=":"q2_spoke_to_zosia","re":true},"^Zosia leads you past crates and cookfires.","\n","^\"Agata used to stand here all day,\" she says, pointing to a post near the fence. \"Stared at the flowers more than she slept. Like she knew they'd...\"","\n","^She shrugs, throat tight.","\n","^\"Infirmary corner there, that's where they kept her,\" she says. \"Guard outside, like she'd run. She never did.\"","\n","^She gestures to a neat bunk with blankets folded regulation-tight.","\n","^\"Corvin's. He was...strict, but not cruel. After they brought Agata back the first time, I heard him shouting with the captain. Said he was no priest, shouldn't be cutting tongues. Next night he was gone. Next morning...\"","\n","^Her gaze drifts toward the field.","\n","^\"Captain says a monster tore him apart,\" she murmurs. \"Maybe it did. But he went out there alone, on purpose.\"","\n","^You file that away.","\n","^\"There's an old herbalist in Rybnik,\" Zosia says as you walk. \"Marta Piolun. Captain sends for her whenever the latrines smell wrong or someone coughs blood. She knows every plant in these parts.\"","\n","^You nod.","\n","^\"Then she'll know the flowers,\" you say, tapping a widowbloom stem. Barbs prick your glove.","\n",{"->":"q2_camp_hub"},{"#f":1}],"q2_janrek_first_meeting":[["ev",true,"/ev",{"VAR=":"q2_spoke_to_janrek","re":true},"ev",true,"/ev",{"VAR=":"janrek_confronted_q2","re":true},"^Captain Janrek Olshanski stands by a brazier, armor polished, cloak immaculate despite the mud. His face is all hard lines and tired eyes, the kind of man war carves rather than breaks.","\n","^\"Witcher,\" he says, voice clipped. \"Good. Maybe you can give my men back their nerve.\"","\n","^\"You need me to kill a beast,\" you say. \"So far I see an execution and a butchered sergeant.\"","\n","^He takes a slow breath.","\n","^\"Agata ran,\" he says. \"Night before last. My men say they saw her by the flowers. Corvin went after a deserter, not an innocent. Neither came back, though. Scouts found their bodies at dawn. Both mauled. Flowers...\"","\n","^He grimaces.","\n","^\"Whatever's nesting in that field is using them as fertilizer. That, not old women's gossip or bathhouse tales, is your concern.\"","\n","^\"Agata's tongue was cut out before her throat,\" you say. \"Neat work. Human. Corvin's cuts are long and lingering. That's someone who likes the sight of blood. I can think of a few people like that.\"","\n","^Janrek's jaw tightens.","\n","^\"You said yourself the flowers are strange,\" he replies. \"Maybe they do the cutting. That's why you're here, mutant. To stop the guessing and end things.\"","\n","ev","str","^Press him about Mila and Stonecross, see how he reacts.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":4},"ev","str","^Let his lies stand. For now. You'll need more leverage later.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-1","flg":4},{"c-0":["\n","^\"You cleared the baths once,\" you say. \"Girl from Rybnik. Birth in the baths. Ended badly, didn't it?\"","\n","^His eyes go flat.","\n","^\"I don't answer to bathhouse gossip,\" he says softly. \"You're here to kill beasts, not slander officers. Push this, and I have you barred from camp.\"","\n","^Hands tighten on nearby sword hilts.","\n",{"->":"q2_camp_hub"},{"#f":5}],"c-1":["^ ","\n","^You shrug.","\n","^\"Fine. I'll hunt your beast. You keep your stories straight.\"","\n",{"->":"q2_camp_hub"},{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"q2_go_to_marta":[["ev",false,"/ev",{"VAR=":"q2_spoke_to_marta","re":true},"^\"Can I come with?\" she asks you. \"I not be a pain, I promise.\"","\n","ev","str","^Let Zosia ride with you to Rybnik.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":4},"ev","str","^Send Zosia back to camp. Travel alone.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-1","flg":4},{"c-0":["\n","^\"Mount up,\" you say. \"You know the way.\"","\n","^Her smile is brief, but real.","\n",{"->":"q2_road_to_rybnik"},{"#f":5}],"c-1":["^ ","\n","^\"You go back,\" you tell her. \"I'll find Rybnik.\"","\n","^She nods, reluctantly. \"Ask Marta...if Agata hurt. When she died.\"","\n",{"->":"q2_road_to_rybnik"},{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"q2_road_to_rybnik":["^Near Rybnik, you hear snarling and a sharp, cracked voice.","\n","^Three wolves circle a ditch where an old, hunched woman stands ankle-deep in mud, skirts hitched, knife in one hand and bundle of herbs in the other. She whacks a wolf on the muzzle with the nettles. She appears to have absolutely no regard for her own life.","\n","^\"I said off, flea-bags!\" she snaps. \"These roots are worth more than your mangy hides.\"","\n","^The wolf recoils, sneezing. Then all three turn their yellow eyes toward you and Roach. You finish things quickly. Steel and snarls, then silence.","\n","^The old woman clicks her tongue.","\n","^\"Oh, now I've got fur in the thyme.\"","\n","^\"Wolves would've had your leg in their teeth,\" you reply.","\n","^She snorts.","\n","^\"And I'd have brewed a tonic from their livers. Waste not.\"","\n","^\"You're Marta,\" you say.","\n","^\"You're a mutant,\" she says. \"Come, witcher. What have you brought me?\"","\n",{"->":"q2_marta_house_entry"},{"#f":1}],"q2_marta_house_entry":["ev",{"VAR?":"q1_mila_locket_found"},"!",{"VAR?":"has_mila_locket"},"!","&&","/ev",[{"->":".^.b","c":true},{"b":["\n","^Rybnik sits comfortable on its hill. Houses tight and solid, fences mended, granaries full. It looks wrong for Velen after having spent so much time in its various hamlets. Too well-fed. Too comfortable.","\n","^Marta's cottage at the edge of town is sturdier than most. Stone foundation, tiled roof, rows of herbs hanging under the eaves, charms over the door.","\n","^Inside, Marta finally takes the flower you've been carrying.","\n",{"->":".^.^.^.9"},null]}],[{"->":".^.b"},{"b":["\n","^Rybnik sits comfortable on its hill. Houses tight and solid, fences mended, granaries full. It looks wrong for Velen after having spent so much time in its various hamlets. Too well-fed. Too comfortable.","\n","^Marta's cottage at the edge of town is sturdier than most. Stone foundation, tiled roof, rows of herbs hanging under the eaves, charms over the door. A birch leans over a crooked fence in a way you've seen before—small and painted.","\n",{"->":".^.^.^.9"},null]}],"nop","\n","ev",{"VAR?":"q1_mila_locket_found"},{"VAR?":"has_mila_locket"},"&&","/ev",[{"->":".^.b","c":true},{"b":["\n","ev","str","^Pause—the cottage matches the miniature in Mila's locket.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":4},{"->":".^.^.^.18"},{"c-0":["^ ","\n",{"->":"q2_marta_locket_scene"},{"#f":5}]}]}],[{"->":".^.b"},{"b":["\n",{"->":"q2_marta_identify_flowers"},{"->":".^.^.^.18"},null]}],"nop","\n",{"#f":1}],"q2_marta_locket_scene":[["^You rein in for a moment, eyeing the roofline, the leaning birch, the fence. Your fingers go to the locket in your satchel. You flip it open. Mila's painted face on one side. This cottage on the other, down to the sag in the roof and the tree.","\n","^\"Nice place,\" you say when you're inside, ducking under low beams. \"Looks familiar.\"","\n","^Marta glances up from hanging herbs.","\n","^\"Plague spared this village more than most,\" she says. \"Houses stand longer when folk don't die in them. One that looks like another's no wonder.\"","\n","ev","str","^Let it go, pocket the locket again.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":4},"ev","str","^Show her the locket, press the connection.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-1","flg":4},{"c-0":["\n","^You let the metal snap shut.","\n","^\"Maybe I've just seen too many crooked fences,\" you say.","\n",{"->":"q2_marta_identify_flowers"},{"#f":5}],"c-1":["\n",{"->":"q2_marta_locket_press"},{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"q2_marta_locket_press":[["^You set the locket on her table, flip it open so the cottage faces her.","\n","^\"Painter didn't guess the fence lean,\" you say. \"Or the birch. Or the roofline. Girl who carried this must be from Rybnik.\"","\n","^Marta goes very still. Her fingers hover over the miniature, not quite touching.","\n","^\"Where'd you get that?\" she asks, voice dry.","\n","^\"A girl named Mila,\" you say. \"In Stonecross.\"","\n","^You can tell in the creased lines of her face that you're not mistaken: their relationship is closer than she's letting on. But there's also pain she's trying to hide.","\n","ev","str","^Press further. Tell her what happened to Mila.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":20},"ev","str","^You can see the pain behind her eyes. You let it go and move on.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-1","flg":20},{"c-0":["\n",{"->":"q2_push_mila"},{"#f":5}],"c-1":["\n",{"->":"q2_marta_identify_flowers"},{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"q2_push_mila":[["^\"She met a Nilfgaardian captain. Got with child. He... had her silenced,\" you say delicately.","\n","^The lines around Marta's mouth deepen. For a moment, the room is only the creak of beams and the soft rattle of drying herbs.","\n","^\"Used to be a girl here,\" she says finally. \"Sat under that birch, watched me dig in the dirt. Said she'd go to the city, make something of herself. Lots of girls say that. Hard to remember all their faces.\"","\n","^Her eyes say otherwise.","\n","ev","str","^Tell her the child lived, last you heard. Then give her the locket.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":4},"ev","str","^Keep the locket and move on to why you came here: the red flowers.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-1","flg":4},{"c-0":["\n","^\"Child lived,\" you say. \"Hidden, last I heard. Safer that way.\"","\n","^Marta's eyes shine, but no tears fall. She closes the locket gently and pushes it back toward you, then pulls it to her breast instead.","\n","^\"Can I keep it?\" she asks.","\n","^You nod.","\n","ev",true,"/ev",{"VAR=":"gave_locket_to_marta","re":true},"ev",false,"/ev",{"VAR=":"has_mila_locket","re":true},"^\"You came about flowers, not ghosts,\" she mutters, visibly shoving grief aside. \"Show me what you dragged in.\"","\n",{"->":"q2_marta_identify_flowers"},{"#f":5}],"c-1":["\n",{"->":"q2_marta_identify_flowers"},{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"q2_marta_identify_flowers":[["ev",true,"/ev",{"VAR=":"q2_spoke_to_marta","re":true},"ev",true,"/ev",{"VAR=":"q2_redcap_identified","re":true},"^Marta finally takes the flower you've been carrying.","\n","^\"We found these chewed up next to two bodies. Growing out of their wounds, too. What part did they play?\"","\n","^She runs a thumb along the stem. A bead of her own blood wells where a barb pricks skin. She sucks it away, unbothered.","\n","^\"See those?\" she says. \"Tiny hooks. You don't eat this unless you like your gums flayed. Anyone tried would spit after one bite.\"","\n","^She rolls the blossom between finger and thumb, sniffing.","\n","^\"Widow's bloom,\" she says. \"Grows best where blood's thick in the soil—battlefields, plague pits, under execution stages.\"","\n","^\"A battle site then. The hill would've been the proper place for one, maybe at one time.\"","\n","^She snorts.","\n","^\"Not a battlefield,\" she says. \"That's where they burned plague dead, years back. From little towns that weren't as lucky as Rybnik.\"","\n","^She tosses the flower back to you.","\n","^\"Hm. Then who chewed these...\"","\n","^\"Human mouth wouldn't get past one bite,\" she says. \"Unless they like the taste of their own blood. You're not hunting poison, witcher. You're hunting something that thinks of blood as a garnish.\"","\n","^Redcaps, you consider. Graveyard imps who chew brambles, revel in blood, haunt killing grounds.","\n","^\"Fits,\" you say. \"Carved Corvin like a roast. Let him bleed slow. Flowers drank. Something else did, too.\"","\n","^\"Should've known,\" Marta mutters. \"This world never leaves graves alone.\"","\n","ev","str","^You have what you need. Head back to the camp.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":4},{"c-0":["^ ","\n",{"->":"q2_return_from_marta"},{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"q2_return_from_marta":[["^You step back out into Rybnik's clean, chill air. Children play in the lane, cheeks flushed with good food. In your mind, plague carts roll past in some other village, where houses didn't stand this long.","\n","^You ride out before you become too comfortable.","\n","ev","str","^Ride back toward Widow's Field to track the redcap.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":4},"ev","str","^Detour to camp first, gauge Janrek's mood before you hunt.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-1","flg":4},{"c-0":["\n",{"->":"q2_track_redcap"},{"#f":5}],"c-1":["\n",{"->":"q2_camp_hub"},{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"q2_track_redcap":["ev",{"VAR?":"q2_redcap_identified"},"!","/ev",[{"->":".^.b","c":true},{"b":["\n","ev",true,"/ev",{"VAR=":"q2_redcap_identified","re":true},{"->":".^.^.^.5"},null]}],"nop","\n","^Back at Widow's Field, the air feels thicker. Petals stick to your boots as, now that you know what you're looking for, you're able to follow the heavy, childlike tracks through the brambles.","\n","^They end at a thick patch of flowers. Bones dangle from stems. Small ones, bird and rat. Larger ones: fingerbones threaded like beads, a chipped bit of Nilfgaardian armor hanging like a wind chime.","\n","^In the center, you find a hatch-door overgrown with flowers. Down inside, a dark hollow lined with stained stones. The air smells of old blood and copper.","\n","^You step in.","\n",{"->":"q2_redcap_first_contact"},{"#f":1}],"q2_redcap_first_contact":[["ev",true,"/ev",{"VAR=":"redcap_alive","re":true},"^Something moves in the hollow. A squat shape unfolds, climbing onto a crude stone throne.","\n","^It's larger than most redcaps you've seen. Much larger. Shoulders thick with corded muscle, arms wiry and strong. Hat and beard matted with dried blood. It chews a widowbloom stem like a man chain-smoking, thorns tearing its gums. Blood trickles down its chin. It grins with pink teeth.","\n","^\"Mmm,\" it says, sniffing. \"Smell steel. Oils. Old kills. You're like me, longshanks. Just politer.\"","\n","ev","str","^Attack immediately. It's a redcap. Don't give it more opportunity than you have already.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":4},"ev","str","^Talk first. Find out what deal it struck for this field.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-1","flg":4},{"c-0":["\n",{"->":"q2_redcap_fight"},{"#f":5}],"c-1":["\n",{"->":"q2_redcap_dialogue"},{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"q2_redcap_dialogue":[["^You keep your sword low.","\n","^\"You don't find a blood-treasure of a field like this on your own,\" you say. \"This is no battlefield. How did you come about this place, redcap?\"","\n","^It spits a leaf spine, licks blood from its lips.","\n","^\"Old woman from village,\" it says. \"Good with plants. Scattered seeds over the fresh graves. Promised I could eat every fool who tread on their graves. I chewed flowers. And I could gorge myself on these blood flowers long as I wanted. Good years, it's been witcher.\"","\n","^It jerks its chin toward the camp.","\n","^\"Then black-tents came. Stomped the blooms. Pissed on my supper. Brought that old hen with them. Cut her throat, tongue first. Left her for me. Came back later, one of them. Took off helm. Cried on her shoulder.\"","\n","^It smiles wider.","\n","^\"Guilt tastes...different,\" it purrs. \"Sweeter. I took my time with that one. Messy business.\"","\n","^\"Sergeant Corvin,\" you say. \"Executed Agata on orders, then came back to weep over what he'd done? You smelled it.\"","\n","^\"Better than wine,\" the redcap croons. \"Old blood in soil was sour. New blood...bubbles on the tongue.\"","\n","^It shifts, restless.","\n","^\"Since then,\" it admits, \"flowers don't fill me like they used to. Tents are so close. Heartbeats everywhere. Hard not to drink.\"","\n","ev","str","^Point out it will be hunted if it keeps taking soldiers.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":4},"ev","str","^Ask if it's willing to spare the soldiers if the camp moves.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-1","flg":4},{"c-0":["\n","^\"Keep feeding on the camp,\" you say, \"and sooner or later they'll send more than one witcher. Or burn the whole field.\"","\n","^It shrugs.","\n","^\"Then I die with a full belly,\" it says. \"But I like my garden. Like my bones. I'd rather keep them.\"","\n",{"->":"q2_redcap_deal_options"},{"#f":5}],"c-1":["\n",{"->":"q2_redcap_deal_options"},{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"q2_redcap_deal_options":[["^\"Here's how this works,\" you say. \"You stop hunting soldiers. They move their camp off your plague-pit. No more executions here. You keep your flowers. They keep their throats.\"","\n","^The redcap gnaws a thorn, thinking.","\n","^\"I'd miss the taste,\" it says. \"But trampled blooms are worse. Boots break stems. Heads break nicer.\"","\n","^It cocks its head.","\n","^\"Move the tents, stop the killings, and I'll hunt only those you bring me,\" it says. \"Offerings. Deserters. Condemned. Meat that won't be missed.\"","\n","^It grins.","\n","^\"Or we can fight now. Your choice, longshanks.\"","\n","ev","str","^Accept the bargain. Plan to force Janrek to move camp.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":4},"ev","str","^Refuse any pact. This thing dies here.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-1","flg":4},"ev","str","^Feign agreement, intending to betray it later.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-2","flg":4},{"c-0":["^ ","\n","ev",true,"/ev",{"VAR=":"redcap_bargain_made","re":true},{"->":"q2_redcap_bargain"},{"#f":5}],"c-1":["\n",{"->":"q2_redcap_fight"},{"#f":5}],"c-2":["^ ","\n","^\"Fine,\" you say. \"I'll talk to the captain.\"","\n","^It laughs softly.","\n","^\"Neither of us are any good at lying, witcher,\" it says. \"Let's see whose lie lasts.\"","\n",{"->":"q2_resolution_hub"},{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"q2_redcap_fight":["ev",false,"/ev",{"VAR=":"redcap_alive","re":true},"ev",true,"/ev",{"VAR=":"q2_redcap_killed","re":true},"^You move first. The redcap dives into the flowers, vanishing beneath a wash of red. Thorny stems whip up around your boots, trying to snare. Something sharp slashes at your calves.","\n","^You stomp roots, carve petals, use Yrden to slow the little brute when it bursts from the ground like a bloody badger. It fights like an addict guarding its last bottle—claws, teeth, improvised blades wrapped in brambles.","\n","^In the end, steel and Signs do what they always do. The redcap falls, hat soaked, blood soaking into the soil that fed it.","\n",{"->":"q2_resolution_hub"},{"#f":1}],"q2_redcap_bargain":["ev",true,"/ev",{"VAR=":"redcap_alive","re":true},"ev",true,"/ev",{"VAR=":"redcap_bargain_made","re":true},"^\"Then we have an understanding,\" you say.","\n","^The redcap hops down from its stone seat, plucks a handful of flowers, chews them thoughtfully.","\n","^\"Move the boots,\" it says. \"Bring me meat now and then. I stay under the petals.\"","\n","^\"Try to be picky,\" you say. \"World has enough corpses without you helping.\"","\n","^It snorts.","\n","^\"World has never needed my help to bleed,\" it says.","\n",{"->":"q2_resolution_hub"},{"#f":1}],"q2_resolution_hub":[["^You stand between field and camp, boots stained red with crushed petals. Behind you, the redcap's den breathes through its flowers. Ahead, Janrek's banners crackle in the wind.","\n","^You have choices.","\n","ev",{"VAR?":"redcap_alive"},"/ev",[{"->":".^.b","c":true},{"b":["\n","ev","str","^Use what you've learned to blackmail Janrek into moving the camp.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":4},{"->":".^.^.^.8"},{"c-0":["\n",{"->":"q2_move_camp_off_field"},{"#f":5}]}]}],"nop","\n","ev",{"VAR?":"redcap_alive"},"/ev",[{"->":".^.b","c":true},{"b":["\n","ev","str","^Leave the redcap as silent guardian, trust fear to keep men off the field.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":4},{"->":".^.^.^.14"},{"c-0":["^ ","\n","^You decide to leave soldiers to their orders and monsters to their hunger. Let rumor and flowers do the work. Over the next few hours, a man or two goes missing. And then a dozen do.","\n",{"->":"q2_after_redcap_decision"},{"#f":5}]}]}],"nop","\n","ev",{"VAR?":"redcap_alive"},"!","/ev",[{"->":".^.b","c":true},{"b":["\n","ev","str","^Confront Janrek about Agata, Corvin, and the deaths, with no monster left to blame.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":4},{"->":".^.^.^.21"},{"c-0":["^ ","\n",{"->":"q2_janrek_final_confrontation"},{"#f":5}]}]}],"nop","\n","ev",{"VAR?":"bannik_alive"},"/ev",[{"->":".^.b","c":true},{"b":["\n","ev","str","^Consider a darker path. Let monsters judge monsters. Lure Janrek to the bannik.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":4},{"->":".^.^.^.27"},{"c-0":["^ ","\n",{"->":"lure_janrek_to_baths"},{"#f":5}]}]}],"nop","\n","ev","str","^Take your coin and leave Janrek to whatever justice the war provides.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":4},{"c-0":["\n",{"->":"q2_mark_complete"},{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"q2_move_camp_off_field":["ev",true,"/ev",{"VAR=":"widow_field_camp_moved","re":true},"^Janrek listens, jaw clenched, as you lay out details he never wanted anyone to stitch together: bathhouse, midwife, flowers, redcap. Agata's execution. Corvin's guilt. The monster you could unleash.","\n","^\"You move your tents off Widow's Field,\" you say quietly, \"stop using it as a place to cut throats, and the thing in the flowers stays sated. Or I leave it there and ride to your general with everything I've heard.\"","\n","^For a long moment, he says nothing. Then he nods, once.","\n","^\"We break camp at first light,\" he mutters. \"Shift to the rocky ground by the ford. My men will curse you for the stones under their backs at night.\"","\n","^\"They can curse me alive,\" you say. \"Better than being fertilizer.\"","\n",{"->":"q2_after_redcap_decision"},{"#f":1}],"q2_after_redcap_decision":[["^Within days, Widow's Field stands empty of tents. Flowers sway in the wind, untrampled. The camp has moved to the rocky ford a ways down the road. Men grumble as they hammer stakes into rock, but fewer wake sweating at night.","\n","^The redcap, if alive, keeps chewing in its ring of stems, content with its bloody flowers and the occasional stray fool.","\n","ev","str","^Confront Janrek one last time about his crimes.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":4},{"c-0":["\n",{"->":"q2_janrek_final_confrontation"},{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"q2_janrek_final_confrontation":[["^You find Janrek alone near the camp's edge, looking toward Widow's Field.","\n","^\"Your midwife didn't run,\" you say. \"She was marched to that hill and executed. Tongue cut out, throat slit. Corvin did it. On your order.\"","\n","^His shoulders stiffen.","\n","^\"War forgives what peace never will,\" he says. \"We needed silence. Order.\"","\n","^\"The dead never had the chance to forgive. Not like they would,\" you reply. \" And I certainly don't.\"","\n","ev","str","^Draw steel. Kill him here and now.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":4},"ev","str","^Turn him over to Nilfgaardian authority.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-1","flg":4},"ev","str","^Deliver him to the bannik.","/str",{"VAR?":"bannik_alive"},"/ev",{"*":".^.c-2","flg":5},"ev","str","^Walk away. Some debts, you leave to the next war.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-3","flg":4},{"c-0":["\n","ev",2,"/ev",{"VAR=":"janrek_state","re":true},"^Steel sings. Men shout. In the end, the captain's black-and-gold lies in the mud like any other corpse.","\n",{"->":"q2_mark_complete"},{"#f":5}],"c-1":["\n","ev",3,"/ev",{"VAR=":"janrek_state","re":true},"^You leave him bound in a magistrate's tent with a neat list of his sins. What Nilfgaard chooses to do with him is its own story.","\n",{"->":"q2_mark_complete"},{"#f":5}],"c-2":["\n",{"->":"lure_janrek_to_baths"},{"#f":5}],"c-3":["\n","^You turn your back on him. The field behind you rustles, red and patient.","\n",{"->":"q2_mark_complete"},{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"q2_mark_complete":["ev",true,"/ev",{"VAR=":"Q2_COMPLETED","re":true},"^Widow's Field remains—red, quiet. Whether its guardian still lives or not, the flowers stand as a carpet over old and new bones alike.","\n",{"->":"q3_old_debts_entry"},{"#f":1}],"lure_janrek_to_baths":["ev",{"VAR?":"bannik_alive"},{"VAR?":"janrek_state"},1,"==","&&","/ev",[{"->":".^.b","c":true},{"b":["\n","ev",true,"/ev",{"VAR=":"bannik_took_janrek","re":true},"ev",4,"/ev",{"VAR=":"janrek_state","re":true},"^It takes time. A favor here, a well-timed warning there. By the time you suggest a \"cleansing\" at Stonecross Baths to break whatever curse haunts his camp, Janrek is tired enough to consider it.","\n","^\"If superstition keeps men from deserting,\" he says, \"I'll soak like a peasant.\"","\n","^The baths are empty when you bring the captain in. You lock the door.","\n","^Steam gathers as he strips, steps into the tub.","\n","^\"You sure this will—\"","\n","^The rest drowns in a rush of water. You do not turn when you hear him thrash. The bannik's laugh sounds like pipes clearing. When you leave, the tub holds only cooling water and a small, floating towel.","\n",{"->":".^.^.^.8"},null]}],"nop","\n",{"->":"q2_mark_complete"},{"#f":1}],"q3_old_debts_entry":[["ev",false,"/ev",{"VAR=":"Q3_COMPLETED","re":true},"^Some time later, on the quiet road leaving the garrison, a mud-splattered boy waves you down. He nearly throws himself under Roach's hooves before handing you a letter from Rybnik. There have been three suicides in the past tenday. Not usually work for a witcher. But the most recent, as of this morning, was  Marta Piolun. The herbalist. Crushed herself in the grindstone of a mill. Left one word on a scrap beside her body.","\n","^Your name. Geralt.","\n","^Whether it was a message...or an accusation, you decide to see for yourself.","\n","ev","str","^Ride to Rybnik.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":4},{"c-0":["\n",{"->":"q3_meet_stas"},{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"q3_meet_stas":[["ev",true,"/ev",{"VAR=":"q3_stas_met","re":true},"^Rybnik looks much as it did before: solid roofs, fat chickens, laughing children in abundance. Not a typical hamlet for a witcher. But the air is tighter. Curtains twitch now. Eyes track you.","\n","^At the well, a thin man with greying beard wrings his cap in his hands.","\n","^\"Witcher?\" he asks. \"Of course. Stas Kurek. Reeve.\"","\n","^You nod. He launches into it like a man trying to outrun his own words.","\n","^\"Katarzyna Brzezina walked into the river with rocks in her pockets,\" he says. \"Old widow. Folk thought she slipped in. Then Mateusz Rak, former alderman, poured lamp oil over himself and lit it. He screamed the village awake. No signs of anyone else. And this morning...Marta Piolun broke into the mill, started the wheel, and put her body to the grindstone.\"","\n","^He swallows.","\n","^\"Door was barred from inside. No struggle. No sign of—\" he glances at your medallion \"—monsters. Only thing strange was a scrap beside the lever. Your name on it.\"","\n","^He lifts his eyes to yours.","\n","^\"Folk are scared, witcher. We thought plague was the worst we'd see. Now our elders are dying one by one, and the last calls on you she crushed herself to death.\"","\n","ev","str","^Ask for the mill key and start at Marta's death scene.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":4},"ev","str","^Ask a few questions about Marta and the others before you go.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-1","flg":4},{"c-0":["^ ","\n",{"->":"q3_mill_investigation"},{"#f":5}],"c-1":["\n","^\"Marta helped half this village stay in the world,\" Stas says. \"Fought every cough, every rash. Katarzyna took in orphans. Mateusz kept books honest even when Nilfgaard came. They weren't...mad. They were our leaders once. Who we looked to in tough times.\"","\n","^He looks toward the distant mill.","\n","^\"If they owed anyone, it wasn't us.\"","\n",{"->":"q3_mill_investigation"},{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"q3_mill_investigation":[["ev",true,"/ev",{"VAR=":"q3_investigated_mill","re":true},"^The mill crouches by the stream, wheel turning slow and steady. Inside, dust motes dance in shafts of light. At another time, you'd think it a beautiful, serene morning in the mill. The air smells of old grain and blood.","\n","^Witcher Senses pick out details.","\n","^The outer door's bar is lifted from the inside. No pry marks on the frame. In the flour on the floor: small, shuffling footprints matching Marta's shoes. No second set. No scuffs from a struggle.","\n","^A stool has been dragged close to the lever that starts the grindstone. Handprints in blood smear the wood. On the grindstone housing, more bloody prints matching Marta's.","\n","^You follow the prints to where they end beneath the wheel. Blood stains rock and wood, dark and flaked. Marta forced herself under the turning stone.","\n","^By the lever, pinned under a rock, lies a scrap of parchment. One word on it, ink blotted and shaky.","\n","^\"Geralt.\"","\n","ev",{"VAR?":"gave_locket_to_marta"},{"VAR?":"q3_locket_recovered"},"!","&&","/ev",[{"->":".^.b","c":true},{"b":["\n","ev",true,"/ev",{"VAR=":"has_mila_locket","re":true},"ev",true,"/ev",{"VAR=":"q3_locket_recovered","re":true},"^Near the wheel, something gleams in the dust. You pick it up.","\n","^Mila's locket. Chain snapped, clasp bent. Marta must have been wearing it when she forced herself under the stone. She died with it pressed to her chest.","\n",{"->":".^.^.^.25"},null]}],"nop","\n","^No sign of claw-marks. No broken boards. No scent of anything but flour, sweat, and blood.","\n","^\"If something killed her,\" you murmur, \"it left no trace.\"","\n","ev","str","^Head to Marta's house next. See what she left behind.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":4},{"c-0":["^ ","\n",{"->":"q3_investigate_marta_house"},{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"q3_investigate_marta_house":[["ev",true,"/ev",{"VAR=":"q3_investigated_marta_house","re":true},"^Marta's house feels wrong without her in it. Herbs hang drying. Jars line shelves in neat rows. Everything is in order. Nothing is at peace.","\n","^On the main table lies a hand-bound book, pages crammed with cramped script and herb smears: Marta's notes.","\n","^You flip through salves and tonics until a strip of red cloth catches your eye, marking a page.","\n","^\"Sight in the Cracks,\" the title reads in her hand. A tonic to let the drinker \"see those who exist in the unseen. Those who ride men like donkeys. Those who collect.\"","\n","^Main ingredient: fresh widowbloom petals. Margin note: \"Dried loses bite. Must be taken from living patch. Field must still drink blood.\"","\n","^She knew something was coming. And she meant someone—maybe you—to see it.","\n","^A door half-hidden behind a curtain leads to a narrow stair down. Locked. The key hangs on a nail by the pantry.","\n","ev","str","^Unlock the door and investigate.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":4},"ev","str","^Stay upstairs. You think you hear someone coming.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-1","flg":4},{"c-0":["\n",{"->":"q3_marta_basement_shrine"},{"#f":5}],"c-1":["^ ","\n",{"->":"q3_irmina_arrives"},{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"q3_marta_basement_shrine":[["ev",true,"/ev",{"VAR=":"q2_entered_basement","re":true},"^The basement smells of dust and old wax. Cobwebs drape low arches. No fresh footprints mark the dirt.","\n","^In the center stands a rough stone block, its top blackened with candle soot and dark, dried stains in a shallow groove. Blood. Years old.","\n","^Four burned-down candle stumps cling to the edges. Beside them lies a withered sprig of widowbloom, color leached to grey.","\n","^You touch the stone. It's cold.","\n","^\"Whatever ritual she called up here,\" you say, \"it was long ago.\"","\n","^Nothing stirs.","\n","ev","str","^Head back upstairs.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":4},{"c-0":["\n",{"->":"q3_irmina_arrives"},{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"q3_irmina_arrives":[["ev",true,"/ev",{"VAR=":"q3_irmina_confronted","re":true},"ev",{"VAR?":"q2_entered_basement"},"!","/ev",[{"->":".^.b","c":true},{"b":["^ An old woman, back hunched, enters the house. She does not knock, nor does she beg your pardon as she steps over your boots and settles into a chair at the kitchen table.",{"->":".^.^.^.9"},null]}],"nop","\n","ev",{"VAR?":"q2_entered_basement"},"/ev",[{"->":".^.b","c":true},{"b":["^ When you come back up, someone is already at Marta's kitchen table. An old woman, back hunched, hands wrapped around a cooling cup of tea.",{"->":".^.^.^.15"},null]}],"nop","\n","^Stas stands nearby, hat twisting in his hands.","\n","^\"Told her to wait outside,\" he says. \"She said if anyone's got a right to sit in Marta's chair, it's her. This is Irmina Sawicka, witcher. Marta's friend.\"","\n","^He looks relieved when you nod dismissal. He flees, leaving you with Irmina and the creak of an empty house.","\n","^She watches you with red-rimmed eyes.","\n","^\"So you came,\" she says. \"Figured you would. Marta was right to write your name. Twenty years ago I'd have ridden to fetch you myself.\"","\n","^You sit opposite her.","\n","ev","str","^Ask about Marta first. Who she was to the village.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":4},"ev","str","^Go straight to the suicides. Why are elders dying like this?","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-1","flg":4},{"c-0":["^ ","\n",{"->":"q3_ask_about_marta"},{"#f":5}],"c-1":["\n",{"->":"q3_plague_bargain_story"},{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"q3_ask_about_marta":[["^Irmina’s fingers tighten around her cup. Her tea has long since gone cold.","\n","^\"Marta?\" she says. \"To the village...\"","\n","^She lets out a dry breath through her nose.","\n","^\"She was the one folk came to when prayers failed. Fever, rot, bad births. She never charged much. Never said no.\"","\n","^She shifts slightly in her chair, winces at some unseen pain, then settles again.","\n","^She looks around the kitchen, taking in the shelves, the jars, the empty space where Marta should be.","\n","^\"Rybnik liked her because she made things work. Didn’t ask why. Just thanked her when the coughing stopped.\"","\n","^A pause.","\n","^\"Funny thing is, witcher...\"","\n","^Her eyes flick to the floor.","\n","^\"She never spoke of saints. Or miracles. Just... costs.\"","\n","^She looks back up at you.","\n","^\"You didn’t come here to talk about how good a woman she was.\"","\n","ev","str","^No. You came because she died screaming.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":4},"ev","str","^No. You came because she left your name by the mill.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-1","flg":4},{"c-0":["\n",{"->":"q3_plague_bargain_story"},{"#f":5}],"c-1":["\n",{"->":"q3_plague_bargain_story"},{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"q3_plague_bargain_story":[["^Irmina stares into her cup a long moment too long.","\n","^\"You’ve seen the mill,\" she says finally.","\n","^\"No struggle. No monster marks. Just old bones choosing ugly ends.\"","\n","^She rubs at the back of her neck, slow, like the joint aches.","\n","^\"Marta always said guilt settles there first.\"","\n","^She exhales.","\n","^\"You want to know why elders are dying like this.\"","\n","^She waits.","\n","ev","str","^Three suicides in ten days isn’t grief. It’s a pattern.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":4},"ev","str","^People don’t choose grindstones unless they’re trying to kill more than themselves.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-1","flg":4},"ev","str","^You sent for a witcher. That means this isn’t just sorrow.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-2","flg":4},{"c-0":["\n",{"->":"q3_plague_bargain_press"},{"#f":5}],"c-1":["^ ","\n",{"->":"q3_plague_bargain_press"},{"#f":5}],"c-2":["\n",{"->":"q3_plague_bargain_press"},{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"q3_plague_bargain_press":[["^Her mouth tightens. She shifts again—sharp this time—then forces herself still.","\n","^\"Ten years ago,\" she says, too quickly, \"plague came down the river. Villages burned their dead in pits. Whole families.\"","\n","^She taps two fingers on the table. Once. Twice.","\n","^\"Rybnik waited. And waited.\"","\n","^Her voice lowers.","\n","^\"When the coughing started here... we prayed. Prayed to the gods, same as everyone else. Nothing answered.\"","\n","^She looks up at you now.","\n","^\"So Marta remembered something older.\"","\n","^The room feels smaller.","\n","ev","str","^What did she remember?","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":4},"ev","str","^What did you two hags summon...","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-1","flg":4},{"c-0":["\n","^\"An old ritual. We prayed to it like the gods. And something answered.\"","\n",{"->":"q3_plague_bargain_reveal_step1"},{"#f":5}],"c-1":["^ ","\n",{"->":"q3_plague_bargain_reveal_step1"},{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"q3_plague_bargain_reveal_step1":[["^\"A Likho,\" she says.","\n","^Irmina pushes her chair back a fraction. The wood scrapes.","\n","^\"In the basement,\" she says. \"Once. We only went at it once.\"","\n","^Her hand trembles as she sets the cup down.","\n","^\"We pricked our thumbs bloody on a rusty coin. Said words you don’t teach children. Or priests.\"","\n","^She swallows.","\n","^\"It promised the sickness would bend around us. Like water around a stone.\"","\n","^Her shoulders sag.","\n","^\"And it did. It said the debt wouldn’t be paid at once,\" Irmina continues. \"Not in fire. Not in fever.\"","\n","^Her hand drifts to her collarbone. Fingers press, as if checking for a necklace or a noose. There is nothing.","\n","^\"Said it would come for us when we were old.\"","\n","^She shifts again. This time she hisses under her breath. Irmina finally looks you straight in the eye.","\n","^\"They walked into rivers. Into fire. Under stone.\" Her voice thins. \"They thought it would die with them. They were trying to kill it.\"","\n","^She slowly reaches behind her neck. Her fingers don’t quite touch her skin. They stop, hovering.","\n","^\"They failed,\" she whispers. Her shoulders jerk—sudden, involuntary. \"Because when their lungs filled, and their skin burned, and their spine snapped... it climbed off. Onto the next pair of old bones that owed it. I felt it come in the night. Embrace me, arms around my throat. It is here with us, now.\"","\n","ev","str","^You didn't call me to solve Marta's murder, did you?","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":4},"ev","str","^What should I do? I don't see anything.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-1","flg":4},"ev","str","^Is that why she sent Mila away? To protect her?","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-2","flg":4},{"c-0":["\n",{"->":"q3_irmina_plea"},{"#f":5}],"c-1":["\n",{"->":"q3_irmina_plea"},{"#f":5}],"c-2":["\n",{"->":"q3_irmina_mila_locket_optional"},{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"q3_irmina_plea":[["^She pushes herself up halfway from the chair, then sags back down—like something yanked her by the spine.","\n","^\"Marta knew,\" she says hoarsely. \"Knew rivers and fire and grindstone weren’t enough, but she tried anyway. She saved certainty for me, by calling you here.\"","\n","^Her eyes flick to your silver sword and leans forward, voice breaking—not loud. Controlled. Terrified.","\n","^\"One clean stroke, witcher, and you could end us. End this. Save they few who are left.\"","\n","^She swallows.","\n","^\"Please. It whispers,\" she says. \"It whispers to me right now. I feel the coldness of it in my ear. Tells me how the plague dead looked, stacked in carts. How they burned. How they screamed when folk in other villages begged for what we got. End this. End my torment!\"","\n","ev","str","^Grant her request. Kill her and whatever rides her in one stroke.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":4},"ev","str","^Refuse to 'swing blind'. Brew Marta's potion to see the Likho first.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-1","flg":4},"ev","str","^Walk away. Let the bargain finish itself.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-2","flg":4},{"c-0":["\n",{"->":"q3_path_mercy_kill"},{"#f":5}],"c-1":["\n","^\"I don't swing at what I can't see,\" you say. \"Not if I can help it.\"","\n","^She huffs.","\n","^\"Then read her book,\" she says. \"She thought of a way. 'Sight in the Cracks.' Drink it, look it in the eye, then swing. Just...swing.\"","\n","ev",true,"/ev",{"VAR=":"q3_likho_potion_learned","re":true},{"->":"q3_path_potion"},{"#f":5}],"c-2":["^ ","\n","^\"You made your bargain,\" you say. \"Sounds like it's come due.\"","\n","^For a moment, she looks almost relieved. Then terrified. Then something like peace settles over her shoulders.","\n","^\"Good,\" she whispers. \"Someone had to say it. This way...it's ours.\"","\n",{"->":"q3_path_let_it_finish"},{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"q3_irmina_mila_locket_optional":["^You turn Mila's locket in your fingers, feeling the weight of it.","\n","^\"Is that why she sent Mila away?\" you ask. \"To keep the Likho from mistaking her for what's owed?\"","\n","^Irmina freezes. Color drains from her face.","\n","^\"You...you know about Mila?\" she whispers.","\n","^You nod.","\n","^\"Girl thought Marta was just a hard mother,\" Irmina says. \"Pushed her to leave, find work, go far. Said she wanted her 'away from old debts.' Never explained. Folk thought she was just proud.\"","\n","^She looks at Marta's empty chair.","\n","^\"Thank the gods Mila wasn't here to see what Marta did,\" she says softly. \"Would've broken her twice.\"","\n",{"->":"q3_irmina_plea"},{"#f":1}],"q3_path_mercy_kill":["ev",{"VAR?":"irmina_alive"},{"VAR?":"likho_alive"},"&&","/ev",[{"->":".^.b","c":true},{"b":["\n","ev",false,"/ev",{"VAR=":"irmina_alive","re":true},"ev",1,"/ev",{"VAR=":"irmina_death_cause","re":true},"ev",false,"/ev",{"VAR=":"likho_alive","re":true},"ev",true,"/ev",{"VAR=":"likho_killed_with_irmina","re":true},"^Irmina stands with effort, turning so her hunched back faces you.","\n","^\"Aim high,\" she says. \"It likes to hide between the shoulder blades when it's afraid.\"","\n","^You draw silver. The room narrows to old bones, hunched shoulders, and a weight you can't see.","\n","^One stroke.","\n","^For a heartbeat, the blade moves through more than flesh. Your medallion flares. A second scream rides under Irmina's—a thin, inhuman wail like rust scraped from iron.","\n","^Then both are gone. She slumps, suddenly light in your arms.","\n","^Footsteps pound at the door. Stas bursts in, sees you standing over Irmina's body with a bloody sword.","\n","^\"What have you done?\" he breathes.","\n","^You wipe the blade.","\n","^\"What you asked,\" you say. \"Stopped an old curse. Now we decide what story you tell.\"","\n",{"->":".^.^.^.6"},null]}],"nop","\n",{"->":"q3_village_truth_choice"},{"#f":1}],"q3_path_potion":[["^If you're going to kill a debt-collector spirit, better to look it in the eye.","\n","^You need the Sight in the Cracks potion.","\n","ev","str","^Go to Widow's Field and gather petals for the potion.","/str",{"VAR?":"q3_likho_potion_brewed"},"!","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":5},"ev","str","^Return to Marta's shrine and confront the Likho.","/str",{"VAR?":"q3_likho_potion_brewed"},"/ev",{"*":".^.c-1","flg":5},{"c-0":["\n",{"->":"q3_collect_widowbloom"},{"#f":5}],"c-1":["^ ","\n",{"->":"q3_likho_confrontation"},{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"q3_collect_widowbloom":["^Back at Widow's Field, the flowers nod as if in greeting. Its quiet under your boots.","\n","ev",{"VAR?":"redcap_alive"},"/ev",[{"->":".^.b","c":true},{"b":["\n","^The redcap emerges from its ring with a stem between its teeth.","\n","^\"Back so soon, longshanks?\" it says.","\n","ev","str","^Trade the fresh corpse for petals.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":4},"ev","str","^Break the pact. Kill the redcap for petals.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-1","flg":4},{"->":".^.^.^.7"},{"c-0":["^ ","\n","^\"You like meat,\" you say. \"I need petals. We can both be happy.\"","\n","^There's always something dead in Velen—a drowners' haul, a bandit who picked the wrong traveler. You drag a recent carcass into the den.","\n","^The redcap claps its bloody hands, delighted, and drags the body under the flowers. When it emerges, it spits a wad of intact petals at your boots.","\n","^\"Chew quick,\" it says. \"Before they wilt.\"","\n","ev",true,"/ev",{"VAR=":"q3_likho_potion_brewed","re":true},{"->":"q3_path_potion"},{"#f":5}],"c-1":["^ ","\n",{"->":"q3_redcap_final_fight"},{"#f":5}]}]}],[{"->":".^.b"},{"b":["\n","^You harvest petals from around the old den. As you pluck them, the world blurs. For a heartbeat you see plague carts, burning pits, faces you don't know screaming.","\n","^Then it's gone. Petals stain your fingers red.","\n","ev",true,"/ev",{"VAR=":"q3_likho_potion_brewed","re":true},{"->":"q3_path_potion"},{"->":".^.^.^.7"},null]}],"nop","\n",{"#f":1}],"q3_redcap_final_fight":["ev",false,"/ev",{"VAR=":"redcap_alive","re":true},"ev",true,"/ev",{"VAR=":"q2_redcap_killed","re":true},"ev",true,"/ev",{"VAR=":"q3_likho_potion_brewed","re":true},"^You put the redcap down for good this time. Flowers drink its blood. You take what you came for.","\n",{"->":"q3_path_potion"},{"#f":1}],"q3_likho_confrontation":[["ev",false,"/ev",{"VAR=":"q3_likho_fight_done","re":true},"^Back in Marta's basement, you set a simple brewing kit on the old stone. Widowbloom petals, water, a few stabilizing herbs from her shelves. The concoction smells of iron and damp stone.","\n","^You drink.","\n","^The world sharpens. Colors wash a little thin. Sounds grow teeth.","\n","^On the stair above, Irmina descends, moving slowly. On her back, clinging like a long child, you finally see it.","\n","^The Likho.","\n","^Thin as a dead branch, skin like dried bark. One huge black eye dominates its face. Its mouth grinds tiny, needle teeth. Its arms loop around Irmina's throat like a noose, legs hanging heavy down her back.","\n","^The eye fixes on you.","\n","^\"Ahhh,\" it says, voice like rusted hinges. \"Someone finally sees. Thought I'd ride this bag of bones into the grave alone.\"","\n","^It loosens its grip and drops heavy to the floor, standing on spidery legs.","\n","^\"You smell like severed threads, witcher,\" it says. \"How many deaths you owe?\"","\n","ev","str","^Talk with it briefly before the fight.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":4},"ev","str","^Skip words—attack.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-1","flg":4},{"c-0":["\n",{"->":"q3_likho_pre_fight_dialogue"},{"#f":5}],"c-1":["\n",{"->":"q3_likho_fight"},{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"q3_likho_pre_fight_dialogue":["^\"You kept your bargain,\" you say. \"Turned the plague away. Collected on the signers. Could've just taken them in their sleep.\"","\n","^It shrugs, long arms swaying.","\n","^\"A pact is a shape,\" it says. \"I like shapes. They begged, I answered. Simple as hung scales. They wanted years without coughing up their guts. I wanted to savor the part where they remember why.\"","\n","^\"Kill you,\" you say, \"and what happens? Plague comes back? Another debt-collector takes your ledger?\"","\n","^It clicks its teeth.","\n","^\"Maybe nothing,\" it says. \"Maybe river of rot finds old path. Maybe it doesn't. You like your odds, witcher?\"","\n","^It grins.","\n","^\"But you didn't drink that pretty brew to talk, did you?\"","\n",{"->":"q3_likho_fight"},{"#f":1}],"q3_likho_fight":[["ev",true,"/ev",{"VAR=":"q3_likho_fight_done","re":true},"ev",false,"/ev",{"VAR=":"likho_alive","re":true},"ev",true,"/ev",{"VAR=":"likho_killed_alone","re":true},"^The Likho moves like spilled ink, darting from shadow to shadow. Its arms lengthen in a blink, hands slapping the floor in front of your boots, trying to drag you down. When it lands on your shoulders, weight hits like a sack of stones, knees locking.","\n","^Yrden slows it, its outline fuzzing but held within the circle. Aard rips it from walls when it tries to cling to Irmina again. Silver bites, but only where the potion lets you see.","\n","^In the end, you catch it mid-leap and drive your blade through that single black eye. It screams—sound slicing through your skull—then collapses into splinters of shadow that evaporate in the cold air.","\n","^Irmina sinks to her knees, gasping as if a yoke has been lifted.","\n","ev","str","^Help Irmina to her feet and see that she lives.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":4},"ev","str","^Let the strain finish her. She dies in the aftermath.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-1","flg":4},{"c-0":["^ ","\n","ev",true,"/ev",{"VAR=":"irmina_alive","re":true},"ev",0,"/ev",{"VAR=":"irmina_death_cause","re":true},"^She grips your arm hard enough to bruise.","\n","^\"Feels...light,\" she murmurs. \"First time in ten years.\"","\n",{"->":"q3_village_truth_choice"},{"#f":5}],"c-1":["\n","ev",false,"/ev",{"VAR=":"irmina_alive","re":true},"ev",3,"/ev",{"VAR=":"irmina_death_cause","re":true},"^Relief hits her like a blow. Her heart, already overburdened, simply stops. She folds where she kneels, a small, tired heap by the old stone.","\n",{"->":"q3_village_truth_choice"},{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"q3_path_let_it_finish":["ev",{"VAR?":"irmina_alive"},{"VAR?":"likho_alive"},"&&","/ev",[{"->":".^.b","c":true},{"b":["\n","ev",false,"/ev",{"VAR=":"irmina_alive","re":true},"ev",2,"/ev",{"VAR=":"irmina_death_cause","re":true},"^You leave Rybnik behind. Sometime later, on another road, a traveler mutters news as he passes.","\n","^\"Old Irmina hanged herself from her rafters,\" he says. \"That's four elders in that village now. Must be something in the water.\"","\n","^You don't need Witcher Senses to picture it—shadow uncoiling from her back as she swings, long legs stepping lightly through Rybnik's lane, looking for the next.","\n",{"->":".^.^.^.6"},null]}],"nop","\n",{"->":"q3_village_truth_choice"},{"#f":1}],"q3_village_truth_choice":[["^Back at the well, Stas meets you again, eyes hollow.","\n","^\"Folk are scared, witcher,\" he says. \"Three elders gone...\" He swallows. \"They'll want to know what you did. Why it's over. Or if it is. What do I tell them?\"","\n","ev","str","^Tell Stas the full truth. The plague bargain, the Likho, everything.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0","flg":4},"ev","str","^Offer a half-truth. Desperate bargain, private price, fewer details.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-1","flg":4},"ev","str","^Lie. Say it was just a curse, their elders were victims, and it's broken now.","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-2","flg":4},{"c-0":["^ ","\n",{"->":"q3_full_truth"},{"#f":5}],"c-1":["^ ","\n",{"->":"q3_half_truth"},{"#f":5}],"c-2":["\n",{"->":"q3_lie_to_village"},{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"q3_full_truth":["ev",3,"/ev",{"VAR=":"rybnik_truth_level","re":true},"^You don't soften it.","\n","^\"They made a bargain,\" you say. \"Marta, Irmina, Katarzyna, Mateusz, a few others. Bought Rybnik's safety with other villages' lives. Something old sat on their backs for ten years, whispering every name it took. They killed themselves trying to crush it. I finished the job.\"","\n","^Stas sags like someone cut his strings.","\n","^\"Folk will tear her charms down,\" he whispers. \"Spit when they pass her door.\"","\n","^\"Maybe,\" you say. \"Maybe they'll also remember they're alive because of her. Both can be true.\"","\n","^Later, you hear mutters in Rybnik's lanes.","\n","^\"Marta the murderess,\" someone says.","\n","^\"Marta who kept plague from our door,\" someone else answers.","\n","^Gravestones go up and get knocked down. Truth hangs heavy over the village.","\n",{"->":"q3_mark_complete"},{"#f":1}],"q3_half_truth":["ev",2,"/ev",{"VAR=":"rybnik_truth_level","re":true},"^\"They made a desperate bargain during the plague,\" you say. \"Turned sickness aside. It cost them, in the end. Something came to collect on what they'd promised. It's dead now.\"","\n","^Stas frowns.","\n","^\"What did it cost others?\" he asks quietly.","\n","^\"Enough that Widow's Field blooms,\" you say. \"Leave it at that.\"","\n","^Later, Rybnik remembers Marta and Irmina as tragic figures—women who paid a private price to keep the village alive. Folk speak their names with a mix of gratitude and unease.","\n",{"->":"q3_mark_complete"},{"#f":1}],"q3_lie_to_village":["ev",1,"/ev",{"VAR=":"rybnik_truth_level","re":true},"^\"It was a curse tied to the old plague years,\" you say. \"Latched onto the oldest, those closest to death. I tracked it. Broke it. Your elders were victims, nothing more.\"","\n","^Stas studies you.","\n","^\"That's enough for them to sleep,\" he says at last. \"Whether it's enough for you...\"","\n","^You don't answer.","\n","^Later, you hear Marta's name invoked over sickbeds, charms of her design hung over doors. Irmina's seat at the well gets a ribbon. Rybnik carries on with its saints untarnished.","\n",{"->":"q3_mark_complete"},{"#f":1}],"q3_mark_complete":["ev",true,"/ev",{"VAR=":"Q3_COMPLETED","re":true},"^Rybnik stays what it is: a village that survived when others didn't. Whether it knows why or not depends on what you chose to say.","\n","^Widow's Field still blooms. Stonecross still steams. Somewhere under it all, debts settle, or wait to be collected in another time, another telling.","\n",{"->":"epilogue"},{"#f":1}],"epilogue":["^The river keeps flowing past Stonecross. Flowers keep nodding on Widow's Field. Children in Rybnik grow up never knowing how close their lungs came to filling with blood.","\n","^You ride on. Another road. Another contract.","\n","^Behind you, three threads of steam, flowers, and old bones knot together, then fade into the fog. Ahead, the world has no shortage of monsters—or people—to keep you in work.","\n","end",{"#f":1}],"global decl":["ev",false,{"VAR=":"Q1_COMPLETED"},false,{"VAR=":"Q2_COMPLETED"},false,{"VAR=":"Q3_COMPLETED"},true,{"VAR=":"bannik_alive"},false,{"VAR=":"bannik_encountered"},false,{"VAR=":"bannik_pause_granted"},false,{"VAR=":"bannik_took_oszkar"},false,{"VAR=":"bannik_took_janrek"},true,{"VAR=":"redcap_alive"},false,{"VAR=":"redcap_bargain_made"},false,{"VAR=":"widow_field_camp_moved"},1,{"VAR=":"janrek_state"},false,{"VAR=":"janrek_confronted_q1"},false,{"VAR=":"janrek_confronted_q2"},true,{"VAR=":"oszkar_alive"},false,{"VAR=":"oszkar_confessed"},false,{"VAR=":"oszkar_given_to_bannik"},false,{"VAR=":"oszkar_turned_in"},false,{"VAR=":"agata_met"},false,{"VAR=":"agata_alive"},false,{"VAR=":"agata_execution_known"},false,{"VAR=":"q1_mila_locket_found"},false,{"VAR=":"has_mila_locket"},false,{"VAR=":"gave_locket_to_marta"},false,{"VAR=":"q3_locket_recovered"},false,{"VAR=":"q1_spoke_to_oszkar_initial"},false,{"VAR=":"q1_saw_soldier_body"},false,{"VAR=":"q1_spoke_to_neyman"},false,{"VAR=":"q1_spoke_to_lida"},false,{"VAR=":"q1_identified_bannik"},false,{"VAR=":"q1_spoke_to_bannik"},false,{"VAR=":"q1_spoke_to_agata"},false,{"VAR=":"q1_oszkar_confronted"},false,{"VAR=":"q1_can_resolve"},false,{"VAR=":"q1_bannik_approach_armed"},false,{"VAR=":"q2_entry_from_agata"},false,{"VAR=":"q2_saw_bodies"},false,{"VAR=":"q2_spoke_to_zosia"},false,{"VAR=":"q2_spoke_to_janrek"},false,{"VAR=":"q2_spoke_to_marta"},false,{"VAR=":"q2_redcap_identified"},false,{"VAR=":"q2_redcap_killed"},false,{"VAR=":"q2_entered_basement"},false,{"VAR=":"q3_stas_met"},false,{"VAR=":"q3_investigated_mill"},false,{"VAR=":"q3_investigated_marta_house"},false,{"VAR=":"q3_likho_potion_learned"},false,{"VAR=":"q3_likho_potion_brewed"},false,{"VAR=":"q3_irmina_confronted"},false,{"VAR=":"q3_irmina_asked_for_death"},false,{"VAR=":"q3_likho_fight_done"},true,{"VAR=":"likho_alive"},false,{"VAR=":"likho_seen"},false,{"VAR=":"likho_killed_with_irmina"},false,{"VAR=":"likho_killed_alone"},true,{"VAR=":"irmina_alive"},0,{"VAR=":"irmina_death_cause"},0,{"VAR=":"rybnik_truth_level"},"/ev","end",null],"#f":1}],"listDefs":{}};